(21, 78, '', '<p><strong>Content:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.vietnam-visa.com/vietnam-5-year-visa-exemption#who\">Who are eligible</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.vietnam-visa.com/vietnam-5-year-visa-exemption#how\">How to apply</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.vietnam-visa.com/vietnam-5-year-visa-exemption#cost\">Visa fees</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.vietnam-visa.com/vietnam-5-year-visa-exemption#time\">Processing time</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Who is Eligible for the Vietnam 5-year Visa Exemption?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>5-year visa exemption for Vietnam is granted to&nbsp;<em><strong>Vietnamese overseas, foreigners who are spouses, children of Vietnamese overseas, or Vietnamese citizens</strong>.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The visa exemption certificate acts as a long-term visa for its holders to visit Vietnam at any time within 5 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"Sample of Vietnam 5 years visa exemption certificate\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://www.vietnam-visa.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/05-years-Vietnam-visa-exemption-certificate-sample.jpg\" width=\"593\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sample of Vietnam 5 years visa exemption certificate</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Important notes:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>No visa is required for travel to Vietnam within 05 years. Those people having a 5-year Vietnam visa exemption certificate are allowed to stay in Vietnam for 180 days at maximum for each visit.</li>\r\n	<li>If they want to stay longer than 180 days without leaving the country, they can&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vietnam-visa.com/vietnam-visa-extension/\">extend visa in Vietnam</a>. The extended duration is up to 6 months.</li>\r\n	<li>The Visa exemption certificate shall be valid for up to 05 years and expires at least 6 months before the expiration of the holder&rsquo;s passport or equivalent paper.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"5 years Vietnam visa exemption summary\" height=\"950\" src=\"https://www.vietnam-visa.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/vietnam-5-year-visa-exemption-certificate-vietnam-visa.png\" width=\"950\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>5 years Vietnam visa exemption summary</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to Get a 5-Year Visa for Vietnam</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You need to follow the two (02) steps below for Vietnam 5 year visa application:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:&nbsp;</strong>Prepare the required documents</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The documents required for applying for a Vietnam 5 year visa exemption depend on the subjects of applications, namely:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Vietnamese overseas; and</li>\r\n	<li>Spouses, children of Vietnamese overseas, or Vietnamese citizens</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For Vietnamese overseas:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To apply for 5 years visa exemption for overseas Vietnamese, the applicant needs to prepare:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>01 5-year Vietnam visa exemption application form (Fill out the form&nbsp;<a href=\"http://mienthithucvk.mofa.gov.vn/%C4%90%C4%83ngk%C3%BD/Khaitr%E1%BB%B1ctuy%E1%BA%BFn/tabid/104/Default.aspx\">here</a>&nbsp;and print it with a barcode on Letter-sized paper</li>\r\n	<li>Passport or equivalent paper or a residence permit granted by a competent agency in the country of residence valid for at least 6 months following the date of arrival in Vietnam;</li>\r\n	<li>Two photos taken recently (white background, straight face, bare head, no colored glasses);</li>\r\n	<li>One certified copy or copy attached to the originals of one of the following papers:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>birth certificate;</li>\r\n		<li>certificate of Vietnamese citizenship;</li>\r\n		<li>the decision for renunciation of Vietnamese citizenship;</li>\r\n		<li>certificate of loss of Vietnamese citizenship;</li>\r\n		<li>Vietnamese passport (valid or invalid)</li>\r\n		<li>Identity Card (valid or invalid);</li>\r\n		<li>latest voter&rsquo;s card;</li>\r\n		<li>Family Register Book;</li>\r\n		<li>Documents issued by competent foreign authorities if they can prove that the person in question has original Vietnamese citizenship or of Vietnamese origin.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>In case of not having documents listed at (4), the following materials could be submitted:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>A guarantee issued by an overseas Vietnamese association from the country of residence.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For foreign spouses &amp; children of overseas Vietnamese or Vietnamese citizens:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To apply for Vietnam 5 year visa exemption for foreign spouses and children of overseas Vietnamese or Vietnamese citizens, the applicant will need to prepare:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>A 5 year Vietnam visa exemption application form (prepared as above if you are in any country other than Vietnam, or download and fill out this&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vietnam-visa.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/vietnam-5-year-visa-exemption-certificate-application-form-NA9.pdf\">Applicant Form NA09</a>&nbsp;if you are in Vietnam);</li>\r\n	<li>Foreign passport valid for at least 6 months following entry date in Vietnam;</li>\r\n	<li>Two photos taken recently (white background, straight face, bare head, no colored glasses;</li>\r\n	<li>One copy attached to originals of one of the following papers which prove the relationship between wives/husbands/children and the Vietnamese overseas/Vietnamese citizens:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Certificate of Marriage</li>\r\n		<li>Certificate of Birth</li>\r\n		<li>Certificate of relationship with father, mother, children;</li>\r\n		<li>Other valid documents as regulated by the Vietnamese Law.</li>\r\n		<li>Decision of Adoption</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:&nbsp;</strong>Submit the documents prepared above to the granting authority:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Agencies competent to grant visa exemption certificates include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Overseas Vietnamese diplomatic missions and consulates (see&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vietnam-visa.com/embassy/\">here</a>&nbsp;for their contact details);</li>\r\n	<li>The Vietnam Immigration Department under the Ministry of Public Security (if you are in Vietnam).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:&nbsp;</strong>Receive your original passport and the 5 years visa exemption certificate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In case you do not know where to start, let us help you. No matter where you are, we can process a Vietnam 5-years visa exemption certificate for you. Spend 1 minute to complete the form below, and we will get back to you shortly.</p>\r\n'),
(22, 78, '', '<h2>5 year Vietnam Visa Exemption Fee</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The cost of getting a 5-year visa exemption for Vietnam depends on the authority with which you apply for it, and the physical address to receive your certificate.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Processing Time of 5-Year Visa Exemption for Vietnam</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Usually, it takes up to 7 days to get your Vietnam 5-year visa exemption certificate issued and granted.</p>\r\n'),
(23, 78, '', '<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Worldwide service.</strong>&nbsp;No matter where you are, Vietnam-visa is the best address to get your Vietnam 5 years visa&nbsp;<strong>EASILY &amp; QUICKLY</strong>!</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Competitive price</strong>. We, for sure, offer the best fee in this regard.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Timely Delivery.</strong><span style=\"font-family:var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ),Sans-serif; font-size:var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size )\">&nbsp;We commit to deliver your documents to your address on time as informed.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ),Sans-serif; font-size:var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size )\"><strong>Easy application</strong></span><span style=\"font-family:var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ),Sans-serif; font-size:var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size )\">. </span><span style=\"font-family:var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ),Sans-serif; font-size:var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size )\"><strong>No presence</strong></span><span style=\"font-family:var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ),Sans-serif; font-size:var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size )\">.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n'),
(25, 80, '', '<p>Vietnam has joined the Asia &ndash;Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) since 2008, the country has become attractive for various business travelers with an APEC Business Travel Card. So,</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What is exactly APEC Business Travel Card?</li>\r\n	<li>Benefits of entering Vietnam with APEC Business Travel Card</li>\r\n	<li>Is it possible to extend stay in Vietnam on APEC business travel card?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>This article makes all these matter clear.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is APEC Business Travel Card?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>According to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.apec.org/\">official website of APEC</a>, APEC Business Travel Card (commonly referred to as an ABTC) is a card issued to eligible business travelers and senior government officials within the APEC region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This card is aimed to make it easier for its holders to travel in and out of other APEC card countries.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What are Benefits of Entering Vietnam with ABTC?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you hold an ABTC, you are exempted from a visa to Vietnam for up to 60 days. It means that, if you hold this type of card, you can visit Vietnam and stay in the country for up to 60 days without a visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition, you, as a holder of APEC Business Travel Card, are also eligible for a fast-track entry into Vietnam.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Is it Possible to Extend Stay in Vietnam on APEC Business Travel Card?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In case your stay duration with 60-day free visa under your ABTC is about to expire and you wish to remain in the country afterwards, you should extend your stay permit right in the country as long as total time of your stay is less than 9 months. Each extension can be valid for up to 3 months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>It&rsquo;s so simple to do the extension with us. You only need to:</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>Send the following documents to our address and pay the extension fee:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your original passport</li>\r\n	<li>Photo your both ABTC sides</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>Get your passport with extended stay within 8 &ndash; 10 working days.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your original passport with new stay permit stamp will be delivered to your address or you can visit our office to pick it up, depending on your choice.</p>\r\n'),
(26, 80, '', '<h2>Why Stay Extension with Vietnam-visa.com?</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>10+ years experience: Since 2007, we have assisted over thousands of ABTC holders to successfully extend their stay in Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>No hidden charge: all the costs of visa extension are clearly communicated with you before the service. We do not charge you anything afterwards.</li>\r\n	<li>Responsibility: We will sign an agreement with rights and obligations of each party concerning the stay extension.</li>\r\n	<li>Convenience: We can support you to extend your stay no matter where you are in Vietnam</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n'),
