(119, 'Phu Quoc Visa Exemption', 'You are eligible for a 30-day Vietnam visa exemption on Phu Quoc no matter whether you are a foreigner or a Vietnamese holding a foreign passport.', '<p>Phu Quoc Island has been a popular destination among leisure travelers due to its stunning landscape adorned with white-sand beaches and vast areas of lush tropical jungle, resulting in an increasing number of visitors to the island. If you are considering a trip to this stunning location, taking approximately 5 minutes to read through this post about the Vietnam visa for Phu Quoc Island would be beneficial.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Do I need a visa to travel to Phu Quoc Island?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If your travel plans in Vietnam only include visiting Phu Quoc Island, you can enjoy a 30-day visa exemption regardless of your nationality. Whether you are a foreigner or a Vietnamese citizen with a foreign passport, you do not need a Vietnam visa if your stay on Phu Quoc Island is for 30 days or less.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prerequisites for Exemption from Phu Quoc Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To enter Phu Quoc without a visa, visitors must meet the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ensure your passport is valid for at least 6 months from your arrival date in Phu Quoc, or renew it before your trip.</li>\r\n	<li>Arrive in Phu Quoc via the Phu Quoc International Airport from an international country. This includes direct, indirect, and layover flights, with Phu Quoc being your final destination along the route. Note that your onward destination can be any country except Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>Your stay on the island should be for less than 30 days. You must provide proof of your departure from Phu Quoc within 30 days, such as a return airplane ticket or the departure date of a cruise ship, to receive a &quot;Visa Exemption Stamp.&quot;</li>\r\n	<li>Enter Phu Quoc by sea (ship or cruise) or by air (airplane) rather than via a land border.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is the Appearance of Phu Quoc Visa Exemption?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/image/images/phu%20quoc%20exemption%20stamp.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. Can I enjoy Phu Quoc visa exemption if I enter the island through Tan Son Nhat International Airport without leaving the transit area?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, you can. The Phu Quoc visa exemption also applies to visitors who arrive at other Vietnam International Airports such as Noi Bai Airport (in Hanoi), Tan Son Nhat Airport (in Ho Chi Minh City), etc., and they do not leave the transit area. In other words, if a visitor flies to other international airports in Vietnam and stays in the transit lounge to take another flight to Phu Quoc Island, they are also exempted from obtaining a Vietnam visa. However, it is advisable to check with the airlines to confirm whether you have to leave the Immigration Area (also known as the transit area) upon arriving at Tan Son Nhat International Airport or not to ensure you can enjoy the visa waiver.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. My passport is set to expire, so what to do to enjoy Phu Quoc visa-free?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You should renew it first prior to traveling to Phu Quoc so as to be eligible for Phu Quoc visa exemption.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. I&rsquo;m a backpacker and planning to cross the river border from Laos to Vietnam, and then head to Phu Quoc. Am I exempted from a Vietnam visa for Phu Quoc Island?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>No, the 30-day visa exemption for Phu Quoc only applies if you travel directly to Phu Quoc by air or sea. If you enter Vietnam through a land/river border, you are considered to be in a different part of Vietnam, and a Vietnam visa is required in this case. Therefore, if you do not apply for a visa, you should not be surprised if you get refused at the border. It is important to ensure you have the appropriate visa before traveling to avoid any issues at the border.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Can I visit Phu Quoc within 15 days without visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q:&nbsp;</strong>I am from a country where its citizens are eligible for a 15-day Vietnam Visa exemption. Can I visit Phu Quoc within 15 days without getting a visa?<br />\r\n<strong>A:</strong>&nbsp;Yes. Phu Quoc is part of Vietnam and your 15-day exemption is applicable to all parts of Vietnam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5. How could I get the 30-day Vietnam Visa exemption for Phu Quoc?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you plan to visit Phu Quoc only and no other place in Vietnam, you are eligible for a 30-day visa waiver specifically for Phu Quoc. Your final destination must be Phu Quoc, and you must depart from Phu Quoc to any foreign country by air within 30 days. Upon arrival in Vietnam, you must present your itinerary to the Immigration officers as proof of your travel plans. This exemption allows you to enjoy your stay in Phu Quoc without the need for a separate visa for this specific visit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>6. Vietnam visa for foreigners staying in Vietnam and going to Phu Quoc</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q:</strong>&nbsp;I am in Vietnam now and my Vietnam Visa is about to expire and/or my current Vietnam Visa Exemption is about to expire. Am I eligible for a 30-day Phu Quoc Visa Exemption while I am in Vietnam?<br />\r\n<strong>A:</strong>No, if you are already in Vietnam and your current Vietnam visa or visa exemption is about to expire, you are not eligible for the 30-day Phu Quoc Visa Exemption. This exemption is only applicable to visitors who arrive directly to Phu Quoc from a foreign country. It does not apply to those who are already in Vietnam and wish to extend their stay or change their visa status. If your visa is expiring, you will need to apply for a visa extension or a new visa to continue your stay in Vietnam legally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>7. How to extend a visa in Phu Quoc?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q:</strong>&nbsp;I entered Phu Quoc using 1-month tourist visa, stayed in for 28 days and now I want to stay in for one more week. I. What should I do if I want to extend my Vietnam visa in Phu Quoc?</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>A:</strong>&nbsp;Please contact with the Immigration Department or call us at +84.904.879.729 for a visa extension.</p>\r\n', 'phu quoc exemption.JPG', 8, 76, '', '2023-04-12 11:04:15', '2023-08-04 23:08:31', 1, '', '', '', '', '', 'Phu Quoc Visa Exemption', 'You are eligible for a 30-day Vietnam visa exemption on Phu Quoc no matter whether you are a foreigner or a Vietnamese holding a foreign passport.', 'phu-quoc-visa-exemption', 'Phu Quoc visa exemption, Vietnam visa exemption', 1, 1),
(120, 'Vietnam Visa Run', 'If you are a frequent traveler who visits Vietnam for only a few days or 30 days and then returns home, maybe you are not aware of the term running Vietnam visa.', '<p>If you are a frequent traveler who visits Vietnam for only a few days or 30 days and then returns home, maybe you are not aware of the term &ldquo;running Vietnam visa&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you plan on staying in Vietnam beyond the duration of your visa, and find it challenging or expensive to obtain a visa extension within the country, a visa run can be an ideal solution. Many expats in Vietnam have utilized this approach to extend their stay in the country at least once, in order to avoid overstaying their visas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now, it&#39;s time to provide you with a comprehensive guide on the concept of a Vietnam visa run, including where to do it and how to carry it out correctly.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is a Vietnam visa run?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In essence, a Vietnam visa run refers to a trip that is necessary for you to undertake if you wish to prolong your stay in Vietnam because your visa is about to expire, and extending it within the country is either not possible or expensive. Essentially, you have to exit Vietnam, travel to a nearby country such as Laos, Cambodia, Thailand, or China, and then return to Vietnam with a fresh visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Read more about <a href=\"https://urgentvisatovietnam.com/which-is-vietnam-visa-extension-or-visa-run\">Vietnam visa run and visa extension</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Advantages and Disadvantages of a Visa Border Run</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Advantages:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cheap price: Opting for a visa border run is a more cost-effective means of extending your visa compared to other methods.</li>\r\n	<li>Variety options: The visa obtained through a visa run is independent of your previous visa, and you have the option to apply for a one-month single entry, one-month multiple entry, three-month single entry, or three-month multiple entry visa, based on your requirements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Disadvantages:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>When doing a visa run, it&#39;s important to note that you cannot stay within the borders of Vietnam. You must exit at the border and then re-enter to obtain a new visa, which can be a time-consuming and effort-intensive process.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Where to do a visa run from Vietnam?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two ways to do your visa run in Vietnam:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Do the visa run via Vietnam international airports</li>\r\n	<li>Do the visa run via land borders</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Below is a compilation of checkpoints from where you can carry out a visa run departing from Vietnam:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" style=\"width:100%\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Airports</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Land borders</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Noi Bai International Airport &ndash; Hanoi</td>\r\n			<td>Bo Y Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Tan Son Nhat International Airport &ndash; HCMC</td>\r\n			<td>Cha Lo Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Da Nang International Airport &ndash; Da Nang</td>\r\n			<td>Cau Treo Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Cat Bi International Airport &ndash; Hai Phong</td>\r\n			<td>Huu Nghi Landport (to China)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Cam Ranh International Airport &ndash; Khanh Hoa</td>\r\n			<td>Ha Tien Landport (to Cambodia)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Phu Quoc International Airport &ndash; Phu Quoc</td>\r\n			<td>Lao Bao Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Lien Khuong International Airport &ndash; Da Lat</td>\r\n			<td>Lao Cai Landport (to China)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Can Tho International Airport &ndash; Can Tho</td>\r\n			<td>La Lay Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Moc Bai Landport (to Cambodia)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Mong Cai Landport (to China)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Nam Can Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Na Meo Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Song Tien Landport (to Cambodia)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Tinh Bien Landport (to Cambodia)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Tay Trang Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Xa Mat Landport (to Cambodia)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Tips:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The most economical visa runs from Hanoi typically involve traveling via Noi Bai Airport to Singapore, Thailand, or Cambodia, which is a popular choice for many.</li>\r\n	<li>For individuals in Saigon or the southern regions of Vietnam, the <strong>Moc Bai border</strong>&nbsp;is a favored option, given that it&#39;s the most affordable, efficient, and convenient method to carry out a visa run from Ho Chi Minh City.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>How does a visa run for Vietnam?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two options available for conducting a visa run - either via airports or land borders. Let&#39;s discuss each of these methods in detail.<br />\r\n<strong>1. Vietnam visa run via international airports</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get your e-visa via email, print it out</li>\r\n	<li>Go to the Vietnam airport for a flight leaving Vietnam</li>\r\n	<li>After completing the customs procedure in that country, you may choose to stay there for a few days or return immediately for a flight back to Vietnam</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2.&nbsp;Visa run to land borders</strong><br />\r\nMany expats in Vietnam favor this method of carrying out a visa run because of its affordability. To undertake a visa run in this manner, you need to adhere to the following steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get the e-visa</li>\r\n	<li>Book a van or a bus or simply drive on your own to the border</li>\r\n	<li>Show your passport once you are at the Vietnam border, and get the Vietnam exit stamp.</li>\r\n	<li>After that, you can get into Laos/Cambodia for a few days&rsquo; trips or go back to the immigration counter to do the exit procedure to get the exit stamp. You&rsquo;re done and successfully outside Laos/Cambodia and ready for a new Vietnamese visa</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>How much is the visa run in Vietnam?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To do a visa run, you need to pay the following items:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>E-visa/Visa approval letter;</li>\r\n	<li>Bus tickets/Air tickets</li>\r\n	<li>Visa fee to Cambodia, Laos, etc. (if required).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Moc Bai visa run<br />\r\nVietnam visa run to Laos</p>\r\n', 'vietnam visa run.JPG', 11, 76, '', '2023-04-12 12:04:59', '2023-04-19 10:04:11', 1, '', '', '', '', '', 'Vietnam Visa Run', 'If you are a frequent traveler who visits Vietnam for only a few days or 30 days and then returns home, maybe you are not aware of the term running Vietnam visa.', 'vietnam-visa-run', 'Vietnam visa run', 1, 1),
(121, 'Which Is Vietnam Visa Extension Or Visa Run', 'To begin with, it\'s important to note that both Vietnam visa extension and Vietnam visa run serve as viable options for foreigners and expats seeking to prolong their stay in Vietnam after their visa has expired.', '<p>To begin with, it&#39;s important to note that both visa extension and visa run serve as viable options for foreigners and expats seeking to prolong their stay in Vietnam after their visa has expired. However, many foreigners are keen on determining which method is the most convenient, straightforward, and affordable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this article, we will provide you with a comprehensive comparison of the entire procedure, analyzing the advantages and disadvantages of each method. This will help you determine which option is best suited for your individual needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vietnam visa extension &amp; Vietnam visa run</h2>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Item</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Visa extension</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Visa run</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Definition</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><a href=\"https://urgentvisatovietnam.com/all-the-information-you-need-to-know-about-vietnam-visa-extension-and-renewal\">Vietnam visa extension</a>&nbsp;this indicates that you will receive a new permit that allows you to extend your stay in Vietnam without the need to leave and re-enter the country.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><a href=\"https://urgentvisatovietnam.com/vietnam-visa-run\">Vietnam visa run</a>&nbsp;is a trip in which you leave Vietnam for another country (usually a neighboring country), and then return to Vietnam with a new visa to continue remaining in Vietnam legally. &nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Where to get</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Inside Vietnam</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>At border gates (land borders or airports)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Form</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>A new stamp on your passport indicating new stay duration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>A new Vietnam visa stamp on your passport with its new validity</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Processing time</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>4 working days (urgent processing) or 8 working days (normal processing)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>3 working days for evisa</li>\r\n				<li>Time for visa run trip</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cost</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Extension fee</li>\r\n				<li>Service fee</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Evisa fee</li>\r\n				<li>Trip cost</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>What to choose Vietnam visa run or visa extension?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Both visa run and visa extension offer their own set of benefits. Your individual circumstances will determine which option is the most suitable for you.<br />\r\n<strong>It will be the visa extension if:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You cannot arrange time to exit Vietnam when your visa expires. or</li>\r\n	<li>You don&rsquo;t want to waste your time for a visa run trip. or</li>\r\n	<li>You want to stay in Vietnam for 1 or 2 weeks after your visa expires as the extension fee for this type of extension is quite reasonable.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>If will be the visa run if:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your extension has reached the limited times and you cannot do it again on your current visa</li>\r\n	<li>You want to save your budget as the border run is quite affordable</li>\r\n	<li>You want to make a short relaxing trip while making a new visa.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We trust that this information serves as a valuable point of reference for you, enabling you to make an informed decision on how to extend your stay in Vietnam.</p>\r\n', 'comparing vietnam visa run and visa extension.JPG', 10, 77, '', '2023-04-12 13:04:58', '2023-04-18 15:04:14', 1, '', '', '', '', '', 'Which Is Vietnam Visa Extension Or Visa Run', 'To begin with, it\'s important to note that both Vietnam visa extension and Vietnam visa run serve as viable options for foreigners and expats seeking to prolong their stay in Vietnam after their visa has expired.', 'which-is-vietnam-visa-extension-or-visa-run', 'vietnam visa run, vietnam visa extension', 1, 1),
(122, 'How To Do Vietnam Visa Run To Laos', 'Is your visa about to expire and you need to do a visa run? Whether you are in Hanoi, Da Nang, or elsewhere, this guide will help you with a proper Vietnam visa run to Laos.', '<p>In many cases, extending your Vietnam visa without leaving the country can be highly convenient. However, the associated cost can be quite high and this method can only be used to extend your visa once. Consequently, many expats in Vietnam prefer the visa run approach due to its low cost and the absence of any limitations on the number of times it can be done.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many people residing in Hanoi, Da Nang, and other provinces of Northern and Central Vietnam opt for a visa run to Laos through Lao Bao and Cau Treo for easy travel, whereas those in Saigon typically prefer Moc Bai.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Preparation Needed Before Departure</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Don&#39;t forget to prepare the following documents for your visa run from Vietnam to Laos:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Make sure you have your original passport with at least 6 months of validity before planning a visa run from Vietnam to Laos.</li>\r\n	<li>A Vietnam evisa</li>\r\n	<li>A Laos evisa (if required)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>A Guide to Doing a Visa Run from Vietnam to Laos Border</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As stated previously, there are two methods for performing a Vietnam land border visa run to Laos, which include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Cau Treo</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Lao Bao</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>It will depend on where you are residing, will you choose Cau Trao or Lao Bao.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>How to go to Cau Treo?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The transportation method to reach the Vietnam-Laos land border for a visa run depends on your place of residence. If you&#39;re in Hanoi, here&#39;s a guide on how to get there.</li>\r\n	<li>While some visa runners prefer to use their own or rented vehicle to reach Cau Treo, most expats opt for the bus due to its affordability, safety, and accessibility.</li>\r\n	<li>If you choose the bus option, you can easily take one from the Nuoc Ngam Bus Station at No.1, Ngoc Hoi, Van Dien, Thanh Tri, Hanoi. You can buy your ticket and reserve your seat at one of three ticket offices: 35B Nguyen Huy Tuong, Nuoc Ngam Bus Station, and 3A Nguyen Gia Thieu.</li>\r\n	<li>Several reliable bus agencies such as Camel, Trekking, and No. 14 Bus Company offer services from Hanoi that typically depart around 6:30 pm to 7:30 pm. Passengers usually spend the night on board and arrive in Laos the following afternoon.</li>\r\n	<li>The bus trip costs approximately VND 250,000 (~ US $12) to VND 500,000 (~US $22), but the fee may change depending on the travel season and the bus company.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>How to go to Lao Bao?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s easy to reach the Lao Bao border gate from Da Nang.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you want a budget-friendly option, taking the public bus can be a good choice, but it will take more time. To get to Lao Bao from Da Nang, you can go to the Da Nang Bus Station and purchase a direct ticket to Lao Bao from the counter. Make sure you get a direct ticket to avoid any unnecessary stops until Dong Da.</li>\r\n	<li>It may take up to 6 hours for this journey by public bus.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'vietnam visa run to laos.JPG', 8, 77, '', '2023-04-12 13:04:27', '2023-04-12 14:04:37', 1, '', '', '', '', '', 'How To Do Vietnam Visa Run To Laos', 'Is your visa about to expire and you need to do a visa run? Whether you are in Hanoi, Da Nang, or elsewhere, this guide will help you with a proper Vietnam visa run to Laos.', 'how-to-do-vietnam-visa-run-to-laos', 'vietnam visa run to lao', 1, 0),
(123, 'Vietnam Visa Run To Moc Bai Border Checkpoint', 'For this purpose, many people opt for a visa run to the Moc Bai border checkpoint in Cambodia, which is considered to be the cheapest option, particularly for those residing in Ho Chi Minh City.', '<p>Many expats in Vietnam are aware that visa extensions within the country can be both expensive and complicated, with the added restriction that visa extensions can only be done once per visa. As a result, those seeking an extended stay in Vietnam often choose to exit and re-enter the country with a new visa. For this purpose, many people opt for a visa run to the Moc Bai border checkpoint in Cambodia, which is considered to be the cheapest option, particularly for those residing in Ho Chi Minh City.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This guide is designed to answer all your questions about doing a Moc Bai visa run, including what you need to prepare before you go, how to do the visa run, how long it takes, and how much it costs. Whether you plan to travel by motorbike or shuttle bus, this guide is for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to Prepare for Your Moc Bai Visa Run?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>What documents are required for a successful Moc Bai border run? Take a look at the following list:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your original passport (valid for at least 06 months following your entry date)</li>\r\n	<li>A Vietnam e-visa</li>\r\n	<li>A Cambodian e-visa (If required)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Guide for executing a Vietnam visa run through the Moc Bai border checkpoint in a correct and efficient manner</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The whole process of getting a visa run done at the Moc Bai border covers the following steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Go&nbsp;to Moc Bai border</li>\r\n	<li>Exiting Vietnam</li>\r\n	<li>Entering &amp; Exiting Cambodia</li>\r\n	<li>Reenter Vietnam with a new stay duration</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1: Go to the Moc Bai border from Ho Chi Minh City</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>By motorbike/private car:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>For most people living in Ho Chi Minh city, the fastest way to reach the Moc Bai border gate by motorbike and private car is to go towards Cu Chi and pick up QL22, keep following the way until reaching the border. The distance is around 70km, depending on where you live in the city.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>By city bus:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Take a blue public bus No.703 at Bus station in Park 23/9 (at the corner of Pham Ngu Lao and Cong Quynh street, opposite to Thai Binh Market). If you want to depart and come back to Saigon on the same day, you should start your border-run early in the day, preferably before 9am, as the last bus leaves Moc Bai around 4 or 5pm. The journey takes about 3 hours.</li>\r\n		<li>Frequency: Departs every 30 minutes. And just go to Moc Bai Border</li>\r\n		<li>Price: 40.000 VND/person (around 2 USD/person/1 way).</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>By private bus:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>If you don&rsquo;t want to take a city bus that stops at various spots, you can book a seat on a private bus in any office on Pham Ngu Lao Street. The price is around US $10 &ndash; 12.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2: Exit Vietnam</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll get to the big Vietnamese building. Walk all the way to the right and keep walking until you see a big wooden booth with a Vietnamese official sitting in it. You&rsquo;ll see a bunch of people waiting in line. You can wait in that line, it will probably take like 30 minutes.<br />\r\nGet the exit stamp onto your passport and then exit the border to Cambodia</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3: Enter &amp; Exit Cambodia</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you get stamped out of Vietnam, you make your way to the Cambodian border checkpoint, around 200m walk. Once here, you go to a small booth where you will show your visa (if you obtained it at the Cambodian embassy/consulate in Vietnam) or pay US$30 for a Cambodian evisa, and fill out the form. After getting stamped, go into the adjacent building to &ldquo;enter Cambodia&rdquo;. Then go across to the exit building, and get your stamp out of Cambodia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4: Re-enter Vietnam</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You walk back and into the building again from the other side. At the Vietnam Immigration building, you then show your passport, and Vietnam evisa.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Tips:</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Take some USD with you, occasionally as an extra tip for the officials at the border, around US $10 (no more), so make sure you have this on you just in case. Plus there are lots of drinks and food stalls where the bus waits so you can grab some food here.</li>\r\n	<li>Prepare the exact amount for visa fees so that you don&rsquo;t get caught out needing change.</li>\r\n	<li>Take some extra clothes because the air-con on the bus can be pretty chilly when you&rsquo;re on it for 3 hours.</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure you won&rsquo;t change your port of doing the visa run, as once you change, you need to get a new visa letter.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Moc Bai Visa Run&nbsp; with our service</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s great that we can help you in case you want to do your visa run at ease and in comfort. We have a full package for a Moc Bai visa run, covering:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Transportation (private car with an English-speaking driver)</li>\r\n	<li>E-visa if required,</li>\r\n	<li>Vietnam &amp; Cambodia immigration support.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nBy using this package, you will be:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Picked up by our driver at your address and taken directly to the Moc Bai Checkpoint on a modern private car,</li>\r\n	<li>Welcomed by our agent at the Moc Bai Checkpoint,</li>\r\n	<li>Escorted to get an exit stamp at Moc Bai checkpoint (Vietnam), a Cambodia visa, and an entry stamp at Ba Vet checkpoint (Cambodia).</li>\r\n	<li>Escorted back to complete the Cambodia exit and Vietnam re-entry procedure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>With our professional team and arrangement, you are guaranteed to have the most comfortable and fastest experience for a Vietnam visa run even</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact us at Hotline/Zalo/WhatsApp/Viber <strong>+84.904.879.729</strong>, email <strong>sale@urgentvisatovietnam.com</strong></p>\r\n', 'vietnam visa run to moc bai border.JPG', 11, 77, '', '2023-04-12 14:04:10', '2023-04-19 09:04:34', 1, '', '', '', '', '', 'Vietnam Visa Run To Moc Bai Border Checkpoint', 'For this purpose, many people opt for a visa run to the Moc Bai border checkpoint in Cambodia, which is considered to be the cheapest option, particularly for those residing in Ho Chi Minh City.', 'vietnam-visa-run-to-moc-bai-border-checkpoint', 'Vietnam visa run at Moc Bai', 1, 1),
(124, 'Vietnam Immigration Blacklist ', 'Millions of foreigners from around the world visit Vietnam for leisure trips or long-term job opportunities. While Vietnam is a wonderful place to stay and enjoy, it\'s essential to adhere to the country\'s visa and immigration laws', '<p>Millions of foreigners from around the world visit Vietnam for leisure trips or long-term job opportunities. While Vietnam is a wonderful place to stay and enjoy, it&#39;s essential to adhere to the country&#39;s visa and immigration laws. Failure to do so may result in your name being added to the Vietnam Immigration Blacklist, which can have severe consequences for your stay and plans in Vietnam. To ensure a smooth and trouble-free experience in Vietnam, it&#39;s crucial to follow the visa and immigration regulations diligently.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is Vietnam Immigration Blacklist?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The term &quot;Vietnam Immigration Blacklist&quot; refers to the list of foreigners who have been deported from Vietnam (if they were present in the country) and are subsequently prohibited from re-entering the country by the Vietnam Immigration Department.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How Vietnam blacklists a foreigner?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are various causes that may name you in the Vietnam Immigration Blacklist, of which, the main ones are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Not adhering to Vietnam visa rules can have serious consequences. Some common violations include:</p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Overstaying your visa without obtaining a visa extension on time.</li>\r\n		<li>Not following the intended purpose of your visa. For instance, entering Vietnam with a tourist visa (DL visa) but engaging in paid work.</li>\r\n		<li>Staying in Vietnam with a non-sponsored business visa.</li>\r\n		<li>These actions may lead to penalties, visa cancellations, and potential inclusion in the Vietnam Immigration Blacklist, which can result in deportation and a ban on re-entry to the country. It is crucial to comply with the visa regulations to avoid any disruptions to your plans in Vietnam.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>You commit any offense in Vietnam.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Consequences of getting blacklisted by Vietnam Immigration</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Being blacklisted by the Vietnam Immigration Department can lead to severe consequences, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Imposition of a substantial fine.</li>\r\n	<li>Immediate deportation from Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>A ban on entry into Vietnam for a period of up to 5 years.</li>\r\n	<li>Your blacklisted status will be shared with all foreign missions of Vietnam and immigration checkpoints, resulting in no possibility of obtaining a visa or entry permit for Vietnam during the ban period.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>It is essential to respect and adhere to the visa and immigration laws of Vietnam to avoid being blacklisted and facing these serious repercussions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you don&rsquo;t want to get blacklisted, do not commit the above acts</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Overstay Vietnam Visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overstaying a Vietnam visa occurs when a foreign national remains in Vietnam beyond the expiration date of their visa. The visa expiration date marks the last day that the individual is legally allowed to stay in the country, and if they remain in Vietnam after this date, it is considered an overstay, they are considered to have overstayed their visa. <a href=\"/overstay-vietnam-visa\">Click here</a> to read more!</p>\r\n', 'vietnam immigration blacklist.JPG', 42, 76, '', '2023-04-21 14:04:57', '2023-08-04 23:08:01', 1, '', '', '', '', '', 'Vietnam Immigration Blacklist ', 'Millions of foreigners from around the world visit Vietnam for leisure trips or long-term job opportunities. While Vietnam is a wonderful place to stay and enjoy, it\'s essential to adhere to the country\'s visa and immigration laws', 'vietnam-immigration-blacklist', 'Vietnam immigration blacklist ', 1, 0),
(125, 'Vietnam Visa Photo Instructions', 'Ensuring that your photo meets the correct requirements is crucial when applying for a Vietnamese visa. While the photo guidelines may not be as complex as other documents, it is essential not to be careless', '<blockquote>\r\n<p>Ensuring that your photo meets the correct requirements is crucial when applying for a Vietnamese visa. While the photo guidelines may not be as complex as other documents, it is essential not to be careless. Using photos that do not meet the qualifications can lead to the rejection of your visa application. Taking the time to provide a proper and qualified photo is a simple yet vital step in the visa application process.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<h2>Do You&nbsp;need photo for Vietnam visa?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>An identification (ID) photo is a compulsory requirement for foreign nationals applying for a Vietnamese visa. Just like any other documents, if the photos do not precisely adhere to the specifications of the Vietnam Immigration Department, it can not only lead to a waste of time but also impact your visa application and entry process. Ensuring that your ID photo meets the prescribed criteria is vital for a smooth and successful visa application experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Photo requirements in below:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:100%\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>&nbsp;Embassy visa</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>1 photo required (4x6cm or 2x2inc)</li>\r\n				<li>1 application form</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><span style=\"color:#000000\">&nbsp;E-visa application</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"color:#000000\">1 photo required (white background/recently taken)</span></li>\r\n				<li><span style=\"color:#000000\">Portrait photo (4x6cm or 2x2inc)</span></li>\r\n				<li><span style=\"color:#000000\">Passport data page (clear and having personal bio information)</span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>&nbsp;Visa on arrival</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>2 photos required (4x6cm or 2x2inc)</li>\r\n				<li>No glass, white background</li>\r\n				<li>Recently taken (no longer than 6 months)</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Photos for visa application</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:100%\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope=\"col\">&nbsp;Sample Photo</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/image/images/women%20photo.png\" /></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/image/images/passport%20photo%20sample.png\" /></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Portrait photo:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Portrait photos: 4x6cm or 2x2inc</li>\r\n	<li>White background with no glasses</li>\r\n	<li>Don&#39;t smile</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Passport photo:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Clear scan with personal bio data</li>\r\n	<li>ICAO lines must be readable</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are photos for?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>For all kinds of visas, no matter whether to Vietnam or other nations, photos are compulsory. Depending on the visa application method, you will be required to prepare 01 or 02 photos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For a traditional visa at Embassy/Consulate, a photo is needed to attach on the visa application form for identification. For visa on arrival, you need to prepare at least 02 photos of which 01 is on the visa application form and 01 is for the presentation at the airport if needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Acceptable photos</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/image/images/Acceptable%20photos.png\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As for visa on arrival, here are regulations for visa photos you need to follow:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>02 photos in passport size (4x6cm or 2x2inc).</li>\r\n	<li>Photos must be the same, taken within 6 months.</li>\r\n	<li>Color photos, printed on photo paper, white or light color background.</li>\r\n	<li>Photos must show the entire face.</li>\r\n	<li>Size from the photo&#39;s top edge to the applicant&#39;s top head in the photo is 0.6 cm, and from the top head to the chin is 3.6cm.</li>\r\n	<li>Applicants wear casual clothes, no uniform, no hats, and no head scarves unless it is a religious rule.</li>\r\n	<li>Applicants must not wear sunglasses or tinted lenses other than prescription glasses unless for health reasons. Applicants must present a medical certificate explaining the wearing of these glasses when taking photos.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Acceptable photos.png', 13, 76, '', '2023-07-17 13:07:02', '2023-08-04 23:08:24', 1, '', '', '', '', '', 'Vietnam Visa Photo Instructions', 'Ensuring that your photo meets the correct requirements is crucial when applying for a Vietnamese visa. While the photo guidelines may not be as complex as other documents, it is essential not to be careless', 'vietnam-visa-photo-instructions', 'Vietnam visa photo', 1, 0);
