(237, 119, 'vn', 'Phu Quoc Visa Exemption', 'You are eligible for a 30-day Vietnam visa exemption on Phu Quoc no matter whether you are a foreigner or a Vietnamese holding a foreign passport.', '<p>Phu Quoc Island has been a popular destination among leisure travelers due to its stunning landscape adorned with white-sand beaches and vast areas of lush tropical jungle, resulting in an increasing number of visitors to the island. If you are considering a trip to this stunning location, taking approximately 5 minutes to read through this post about the Vietnam visa for Phu Quoc Island would be beneficial.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Do I need a visa to travel to Phu Quoc Island?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If your travel plans in Vietnam only include visiting Phu Quoc Island, you can enjoy a 30-day visa exemption regardless of your nationality. Whether you are a foreigner or a Vietnamese citizen with a foreign passport, you do not need a Vietnam visa if your stay on Phu Quoc Island is for 30 days or less.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prerequisites for Exemption from Phu Quoc Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To enter Phu Quoc without a visa, visitors must meet the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ensure your passport is valid for at least 6 months from your arrival date in Phu Quoc, or renew it before your trip.</li>\r\n	<li>Arrive in Phu Quoc via the Phu Quoc International Airport from an international country. This includes direct, indirect, and layover flights, with Phu Quoc being your final destination along the route. Note that your onward destination can be any country except Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>Your stay on the island should be for less than 30 days. You must provide proof of your departure from Phu Quoc within 30 days, such as a return airplane ticket or the departure date of a cruise ship, to receive a &quot;Visa Exemption Stamp.&quot;</li>\r\n	<li>Enter Phu Quoc by sea (ship or cruise) or by air (airplane) rather than via a land border.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is the Appearance of Phu Quoc Visa Exemption?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/image/images/phu%20quoc%20exemption%20stamp.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. Can I enjoy Phu Quoc visa exemption if I enter the island through Tan Son Nhat International Airport without leaving the transit area?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, you can. The Phu Quoc visa exemption also applies to visitors who arrive at other Vietnam International Airports such as Noi Bai Airport (in Hanoi), Tan Son Nhat Airport (in Ho Chi Minh City), etc., and they do not leave the transit area. In other words, if a visitor flies to other international airports in Vietnam and stays in the transit lounge to take another flight to Phu Quoc Island, they are also exempted from obtaining a Vietnam visa. However, it is advisable to check with the airlines to confirm whether you have to leave the Immigration Area (also known as the transit area) upon arriving at Tan Son Nhat International Airport or not to ensure you can enjoy the visa waiver.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. My passport is set to expire, so what to do to enjoy Phu Quoc visa-free?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You should renew it first prior to traveling to Phu Quoc so as to be eligible for Phu Quoc visa exemption.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. I&rsquo;m a backpacker and planning to cross the river border from Laos to Vietnam, and then head to Phu Quoc. Am I exempted from a Vietnam visa for Phu Quoc Island?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>No, the 30-day visa exemption for Phu Quoc only applies if you travel directly to Phu Quoc by air or sea. If you enter Vietnam through a land/river border, you are considered to be in a different part of Vietnam, and a Vietnam visa is required in this case. Therefore, if you do not apply for a visa, you should not be surprised if you get refused at the border. It is important to ensure you have the appropriate visa before traveling to avoid any issues at the border.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Can I visit Phu Quoc within 15 days without visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q:&nbsp;</strong>I am from a country where its citizens are eligible for a 15-day Vietnam Visa exemption. Can I visit Phu Quoc within 15 days without getting a visa?<br />\r\n<strong>A:</strong>&nbsp;Yes. Phu Quoc is part of Vietnam and your 15-day exemption is applicable to all parts of Vietnam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5. How could I get the 30-day Vietnam Visa exemption for Phu Quoc?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you plan to visit Phu Quoc only and no other place in Vietnam, you are eligible for a 30-day visa waiver specifically for Phu Quoc. Your final destination must be Phu Quoc, and you must depart from Phu Quoc to any foreign country by air within 30 days. Upon arrival in Vietnam, you must present your itinerary to the Immigration officers as proof of your travel plans. This exemption allows you to enjoy your stay in Phu Quoc without the need for a separate visa for this specific visit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>6. Vietnam visa for foreigners staying in Vietnam and going to Phu Quoc</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q:</strong>&nbsp;I am in Vietnam now and my Vietnam Visa is about to expire and/or my current Vietnam Visa Exemption is about to expire. Am I eligible for a 30-day Phu Quoc Visa Exemption while I am in Vietnam?<br />\r\n<strong>A:</strong>No, if you are already in Vietnam and your current Vietnam visa or visa exemption is about to expire, you are not eligible for the 30-day Phu Quoc Visa Exemption. This exemption is only applicable to visitors who arrive directly to Phu Quoc from a foreign country. It does not apply to those who are already in Vietnam and wish to extend their stay or change their visa status. If your visa is expiring, you will need to apply for a visa extension or a new visa to continue your stay in Vietnam legally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>7. How to extend a visa in Phu Quoc?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q:</strong>&nbsp;I entered Phu Quoc using 1-month tourist visa, stayed in for 28 days and now I want to stay in for one more week. I. What should I do if I want to extend my Vietnam visa in Phu Quoc?</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>A:</strong>&nbsp;Please contact with the Immigration Department or call us at +84.904.879.729 for a visa extension.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 'phu-quoc-visa-exemption', 'Phu Quoc Visa Exemption', 'You are eligible for a 30-day Vietnam visa exemption on Phu Quoc no matter whether you are a foreigner or a Vietnamese holding a foreign passport.', 'Phu Quoc visa exemption, Vietnam visa exemption'),
(238, 119, 'en', 'english version Phu Quoc Visa Exemption', 'english version You are eligible for a 30-day Vietnam visa exemption on Phu Quoc no matter whether you are a foreigner or a Vietnamese holding a foreign passport.', 'english version <p>Phu Quoc Island has been a popular destination among leisure travelers due to its stunning landscape adorned with white-sand beaches and vast areas of lush tropical jungle, resulting in an increasing number of visitors to the island. If you are considering a trip to this stunning location, taking approximately 5 minutes to read through this post about the Vietnam visa for Phu Quoc Island would be beneficial.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 'en-phu-quoc-visa-exemption', 'Phu Quoc Visa Exemption', 'You are eligible for a 30-day Vietnam visa exemption on Phu Quoc no matter whether you are a foreigner or a Vietnamese holding a foreign passport.', 'Phu Quoc visa exemption, Vietnam visa exemption'),
(239, 120, 'vn', 'Vietnam Visa Run', 'If you are a frequent traveler who visits Vietnam for only a few days or 30 days and then returns home, maybe you are not aware of the term running Vietnam visa.', '<p>If you are a frequent traveler who visits Vietnam for only a few days or 30 days and then returns home, maybe you are not aware of the term &ldquo;running Vietnam visa&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you plan on staying in Vietnam beyond the duration of your visa, and find it challenging or expensive to obtain a visa extension within the country, a visa run can be an ideal solution. Many expats in Vietnam have utilized this approach to extend their stay in the country at least once, in order to avoid overstaying their visas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now, it&#39;s time to provide you with a comprehensive guide on the concept of a Vietnam visa run, including where to do it and how to carry it out correctly.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is a Vietnam visa run?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In essence, a Vietnam visa run refers to a trip that is necessary for you to undertake if you wish to prolong your stay in Vietnam because your visa is about to expire, and extending it within the country is either not possible or expensive. Essentially, you have to exit Vietnam, travel to a nearby country such as Laos, Cambodia, Thailand, or China, and then return to Vietnam with a fresh visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Read more about <a href=\"https://urgentvisatovietnam.com/which-is-vietnam-visa-extension-or-visa-run\">Vietnam visa run and visa extension</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Advantages and Disadvantages of a Visa Border Run</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Advantages:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cheap price: Opting for a visa border run is a more cost-effective means of extending your visa compared to other methods.</li>\r\n	<li>Variety options: The visa obtained through a visa run is independent of your previous visa, and you have the option to apply for a one-month single entry, one-month multiple entry, three-month single entry, or three-month multiple entry visa, based on your requirements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Disadvantages:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>When doing a visa run, it&#39;s important to note that you cannot stay within the borders of Vietnam. You must exit at the border and then re-enter to obtain a new visa, which can be a time-consuming and effort-intensive process.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Where to do a visa run from Vietnam?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two ways to do your visa run in Vietnam:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Do the visa run via Vietnam international airports</li>\r\n	<li>Do the visa run via land borders</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Below is a compilation of checkpoints from where you can carry out a visa run departing from Vietnam:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" style=\"width:100%\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Airports</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Land borders</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Noi Bai International Airport &ndash; Hanoi</td>\r\n			<td>Bo Y Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Tan Son Nhat International Airport &ndash; HCMC</td>\r\n			<td>Cha Lo Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Da Nang International Airport &ndash; Da Nang</td>\r\n			<td>Cau Treo Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Cat Bi International Airport &ndash; Hai Phong</td>\r\n			<td>Huu Nghi Landport (to China)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Cam Ranh International Airport &ndash; Khanh Hoa</td>\r\n			<td>Ha Tien Landport (to Cambodia)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Phu Quoc International Airport &ndash; Phu Quoc</td>\r\n			<td>Lao Bao Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Lien Khuong International Airport &ndash; Da Lat</td>\r\n			<td>Lao Cai Landport (to China)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Can Tho International Airport &ndash; Can Tho</td>\r\n			<td>La Lay Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Moc Bai Landport (to Cambodia)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Mong Cai Landport (to China)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Nam Can Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Na Meo Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Song Tien Landport (to Cambodia)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Tinh Bien Landport (to Cambodia)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Tay Trang Landport (to Laos)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Xa Mat Landport (to Cambodia)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Tips:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The most economical visa runs from Hanoi typically involve traveling via Noi Bai Airport to Singapore, Thailand, or Cambodia, which is a popular choice for many.</li>\r\n	<li>For individuals in Saigon or the southern regions of Vietnam, the <strong>Moc Bai border</strong>&nbsp;is a favored option, given that it&#39;s the most affordable, efficient, and convenient method to carry out a visa run from Ho Chi Minh City.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>How does a visa run for Vietnam?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two options available for conducting a visa run - either via airports or land borders. Let&#39;s discuss each of these methods in detail.<br />\r\n<strong>1. Vietnam visa run via international airports</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get your e-visa via email, print it out</li>\r\n	<li>Go to the Vietnam airport for a flight leaving Vietnam</li>\r\n	<li>After completing the customs procedure in that country, you may choose to stay there for a few days or return immediately for a flight back to Vietnam</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2.&nbsp;Visa run to land borders</strong><br />\r\nMany expats in Vietnam favor this method of carrying out a visa run because of its affordability. To undertake a visa run in this manner, you need to adhere to the following steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get the e-visa</li>\r\n	<li>Book a van or a bus or simply drive on your own to the border</li>\r\n	<li>Show your passport once you are at the Vietnam border, and get the Vietnam exit stamp.</li>\r\n	<li>After that, you can get into Laos/Cambodia for a few days&rsquo; trips or go back to the immigration counter to do the exit procedure to get the exit stamp. You&rsquo;re done and successfully outside Laos/Cambodia and ready for a new Vietnamese visa</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>How much is the visa run in Vietnam?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To do a visa run, you need to pay the following items:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>E-visa/Visa approval letter;</li>\r\n	<li>Bus tickets/Air tickets</li>\r\n	<li>Visa fee to Cambodia, Laos, etc. (if required).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Moc Bai visa run<br />\r\nVietnam visa run to Laos</p>\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 'vietnam-visa-run', 'Vietnam Visa Run', 'If you are a frequent traveler who visits Vietnam for only a few days or 30 days and then returns home, maybe you are not aware of the term running Vietnam visa.', 'Vietnam visa run'),
