><a href=\"#\">Venezuela</a></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">Yes</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 'en-vietnam-evisa-eligible-countries', 'Vietnam Evisa Eligible Countries', '', ''),
(253, 127, 'vn', 'Vietnam Evisa Ports of Entry and Checkpoints', 'Vietnam e-visa is currently accepted at 33 international checkpoints including airports, seaports and land border gates. Below you will find a list of eligible ports of entry with map and detailed guide.', '<blockquote>\r\n<p>Vietnam e-visa is currently accepted at 33 international checkpoints including airports, seaports and land border gates. Below you will find a list of eligible ports of entry with map and detailed guide.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<h2>International Airports</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Noi Bai Int Airport (HAN) - Hanoi / Airport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Noi Bai Airport (IATA airport code: HAN) is the second largest international airport in Vietnam</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 18km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 1155km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Cat Bi Int Airport (HPH) - Hai Phong / Airport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Cat Bi Airport, also known as Cat Bi International Airport, is located 5km from the center of Hai Phong city.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 95km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 1107km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Cam Ranh Int Airport (CXR) - Nha Trang / Airport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Cam Ranh International Airport is located on Nguyen Tat Thanh Road, in Cam Ranh Peninsula, Cam Ranh City, Khanh Hoa Province.<br />\r\nDistance to Hanoi: 1064km<br />\r\nDistance to Ho Chi Minh city: 309km</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Can Tho International Airport (VCA)- Can Tho / Airport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Can Tho International Airport is located at 179B Le Hong Phong Street, Tra An Ward, Binh Thuy District, Can Tho.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 1215km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 132km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Da Nang International Airport (DAD)- Da Nang / Airport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Da Nang International Airport is the main operating hub for airlines such as Vietnam Airlines, Pacific Airlines, Vietjet Air, Bamboo Airways, and many other airlines.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 606km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 604km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>6. Phu Bai Int Airport (HUI)- Hue / Airport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Phu Bai International Airport is an important airport of Vietnam, located in the south of Hue City, Thua Thien Hue Province.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 552km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 628km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>7. Phu Quoc International Airport (PQC)- Phu Quoc / Airport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Phu Quoc international airport is located in the south of Phu Quoc Island, in Duong To Commune, Phu Quoc District.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 1222km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 300km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>8. Tan Son Nhat Int Airport (SGN) - Ho Chi Minh City / Airport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Tan Son Nhat Airport is one of the airports with the largest operating capacity in Vietnam.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 1137km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 0km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Landports</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Bo Y Landport- Kon Tum / Landport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Bo Y Landport is the end point of National Highway 40 in Vietnam, connecting with Route 11 of Laos.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 727km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 441km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Cha Lo Landport- Quang Binh / Landport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Cha Lo is the name of a village located in Dan Hoa commune, Minh Hoa district, Quang Binh province. That familiar place name is also the name of a border guard station and an international border gate.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 374km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 765km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Cau Treo Landport- Ha Tinh / Landport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Cau Treo Landport (Huong Son - Ha Tinh) is a gateway for trade between Vietnam and Laos.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 304km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 853km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Huu Nghi Landport- Lang Son / Landport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Huu Nghi Landport is an international border gate of Vietnam located on the Vietnam - China border, the connecting point of the Nanning - Hanoi expressway.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 136km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 1235km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Ha Tien Landport- Kien Giang / Landport</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Located about 7 km from Ha Tien town, Xa Xia Border Gate has become Ha Tien international border gate and a famous tourist attraction in Kien Giang for a long time.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 1186km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 245km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>6. Lao Bao Landport- Quang Tri / Landport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Lao Bao landport, located in Huong Hoa district (Quang Tri province), is a typical and exemplary border gate on the Vietnam - Laos border line.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 497km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 642km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>7. Lao Cai Landport- Lao Cai / Landport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Lao Cai Landport conducts trade through the Ho Bridge (Ho Kieu) that spans the Nậm Thi river, and reaches the international border gate of Ha Khau.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 252km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 1325km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>8. La Lay Landport- Quang Tri / Landport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>La Lay international border gate (Dakrong district, Quang Tri province) connects 4 provinces in southern Laos and northeastern Thailand with seaports in Central Vietnam.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 538km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 609km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>8. Moc Bai Landport- Tay Ninh / Landport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Moc Bai Landort in Tay Ninh is the largest land border gate in the South, which has been operational since 2004.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 1105km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 60km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>9. Mong Cai Landport- Quang Ninh / Landport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Mong Cai Border Gate is not only a major trade route in the economic and commercial sector, but it also holds great significance in fostering the friendship between Vietnam and China.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 227km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 1194km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>10. Nam Can Landport- Nghe An / Landport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Nam Can Border Gate is an international border gate located in Tien Tieu village, Nam Can commune, Ky Son district, which facilitates trade and commerce with Namkan Border Gate in Laos.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 254km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 996km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>11. Na Meo Landport- Thanh Hoa / Landport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Located at the end point of National Highway 217 in Quan Son district, Thanh Hoa province, Na Meo International Border Gate and Nam Xoi Border Gate in Vieng Xay district, Houaphanh province serve as important trade gateways between Vietnam and Laos.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 153km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 1071km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>12. Song Tien Landport- An Giang / Landport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Song Tien International Border Gate is located in Vinh Xuong commune, Tan Chau district, An Giang province, Vietnam.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 1125km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 162km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>11. Tinh Bien Landport- An Giang / Landport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Tinh Bien Border Gate is located in Tinh Bien town, Tinh Bien district, An Giang province, Vietnam.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 1161km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 190km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>12. Tay Trang Landport- Dien Bien / Landport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Tay Trang Landport is highly regarded for its potential in the economic, cultural, and social development strategy of Dien Bien province.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 304km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 1219km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>13. Xa Mat Landport- Tay Ninh / Landport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Xa Mat Border Gate is the gateway of Tay Ninh province and plays a crucial role in promoting trade exchange, as well as building and developing the foreign economic relations.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 1040km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 120km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Seaports</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Chan May Seaport- Hue / Seaport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Chan May seaport is the main port on the sea route connecting Singapore, the Philippines, and Hong Kong (China). Moreover, Chan May port is located in the central position of Vietnam, between the two largest cities in Central Vietnam, Hue and Danang.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 571km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 628km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Da Nang Seaport- Da Nang / Seaport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Located in Da Nang Bay with an area of ​​12km2 and a convenient transportation system, Da Nang Port is currently an important link in the logistics service chain of the Central Vietnam region.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 606km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 606km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Duong Dong Seaport- Kien Giang / Seaport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Duong Dong Seaort is a location classified in the Favorites list, is located at 3 Bach Dang Street, Phu Quoc, Kien Giang.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 1217km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 303km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Hon Gai Seaport- Quang Ninh / Seaport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Hon Gai Seaport is located in a prime location in the center of Ha Long city, Quang Ninh, facing the Bai Chay tourist area.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 128km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 1123km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Hai Phong Seaport- Hai Phong / Seaport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Haiphong Port is a national-level general port cluster, the largest in the North and ranked second after Saigon Port.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 91km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 1112km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>6. Nha Trang Seaport- Nha Trang / Seaport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Nha Trang Port is a sea port located in Nha Trang Bay, Khanh Hoa province. It is a cargo port combined with tourism and an important transportation hub by sea for Nha Trang city in particular and the South Central region in general.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 1044km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 319km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>7. Quy Nhon Seaport- Binh Dinh / Seaport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Quy Nhon Port is a national-level general port and a Class 1 regional gateway port of the South Central Coast seaport group, located in Quy Nhon Bay. It is sheltered by Phuong Mai Peninsula, with less wind and is very convenient for ships to anchor and load and unload cargo year-round.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 883km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 432km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>8. Ho Chi Minh City Seaport- Ho Chi Minh city / Seaport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Port of Ho Chi Minh City continues to hold the 21st position in the top 30 best-performing ports by cargo volume in 2022, as announced by maritime research organization Alphaliner.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 1143km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 16km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>9. Vung Tau Seaport- Vung Tau / Seaport</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Vung Tau Seaport is planned as a seaport gateway in the South of the country and is the center of Vietnam&#39;s and the world&#39;s shipping routes</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Distance to Hanoi: 1186km</li>\r\n	<li>Distance to Ho Chi Minh city: 71km</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 'vietnam-evisa-ports-of-entry-and-checkpoints', 'Vietnam Evisa Ports of Entry and Checkpoints', 'Vietnam e-visa is currently accepted at 33 international checkpoints including airports, seapor