(73, 'Assistance in obtaining work permits for foreign individuals working in Vietnam', 'Vietnam has emerged as one of the most attractive destinations for foreign investors and professionals seeking new opportunities. However, the process of obtaining a work permit in Vietnam can be daunting, especially for those unfamiliar with the country\'s regulations and procedures', '<p>Vietnam has emerged as one of the most attractive destinations for foreign investors and professionals seeking new opportunities. However, the process of obtaining a work permit in Vietnam can be daunting, especially for those unfamiliar with the country&#39;s regulations and procedures.<br />\r\nIn this article, we will guide you through the process of obtaining a work permit in Vietnam, covering everything from eligibility requirements to application procedures and common mistakes to avoid. So, whether you&#39;re a business owner looking to employ foreign talent or an individual seeking employment opportunities in Vietnam, read on to learn everything you need to know about obtaining a work permit.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Eligibility Requirements for Vietnam Work Permit</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Foreigners who wish to work in Vietnam are required to obtain a work permit, with few exceptions. The eligibility criteria for a work permit in Vietnam are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The foreigner must be 18 years or older.</li>\r\n	<li>The foreigner must have a valid passport with at least six months of validity remaining.</li>\r\n	<li>The foreigner must be healthy and not suffer from any contagious diseases.</li>\r\n	<li>The foreigner must have no criminal record or any record of violation of Vietnamese law.</li>\r\n	<li>The foreigner must have a job offer from a Vietnamese company or organization.</li>\r\n	<li>The foreigner must meet the qualifications and requirements for the job.</li>\r\n	<li>Application Procedures for Vietnam Work Permit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The process of obtaining a work permit in Vietnam can be time-consuming, so it&#39;s important to start the application process as early as possible. Here are the steps to follow:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1: Apply for a Work Permit Application Form</strong><br />\r\nThe first step in the application process is to obtain a work permit application form. This form can be obtained from the Department of Labor, Invalids and Social Affairs (DOLISA) or downloaded from their website.<br />\r\n<strong>Step 2: Gather Required Documents</strong><br />\r\nThe next step is to gather all the necessary documents for the application, which include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A valid passport</li>\r\n	<li>A certified copy of the applicant&#39;s highest degree</li>\r\n	<li>A certified copy of the applicant&#39;s criminal record</li>\r\n	<li>A medical certificate issued by a Vietnamese or foreign medical facility</li>\r\n	<li>A job offer letter from a Vietnamese company or organization</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3: Submit the Application</strong><br />\r\nOnce all the required documents are gathered, the application should be submitted to the DOLISA in the city or province where the applicant plans to work. The processing time for a work permit application is typically five working days.<br />\r\n<strong>Step 4: Receive the Work Permit</strong><br />\r\nIf the application is approved, the applicant will receive a work permit valid for up to two years, depending on the length of the employment contract. The work permit can be renewed after its expiry.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Common Mistakes to Avoid When Applying for Vietnam Work Permit</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The process of obtaining a work permit in Vietnam can be complex, and there are some common mistakes that applicants should avoid:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Failing to meet eligibility criteria.</li>\r\n	<li>Not having all the required documents or submitting incomplete documents.</li>\r\n	<li>Applying for a job that does not match the qualifications and requirements of the work permit.</li>\r\n	<li>Failing to submit the application within the required time frame.</li>\r\n	<li>Applying for a work permit with an unregistered company.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vietnam Work Permit Service for Foreigners</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Obtaining a work permit in Vietnam can be a challenging task, especially for those unfamiliar with the country&#39;s regulations and procedures. However, with the help of a reputable work permit service provider, the process can be much smoother and stress-free.<br />\r\nA professional work permit service provider can assist with the entire process of obtaining a work permit, from preparing and submitting the application to following up with the relevant authorities. This can save applicants a lot of time and effort, allowing them to focus on their work or other important matters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Service of making Vietnamese work permits for foreigners of Urgentvisatovietnam.com</strong><br />\r\nForeigners who wish to work permanently in Vietnam for a Vietnamese company, organization, or individual, or a company with foreign investment, are required to obtain a work permit unless they are eligible for a work permit exemption. However, the application process can be confusing due to frequent changes in the law and the complicated procedures involved in obtaining a work permit.<br />\r\nTo help simplify the process, Urgentvisatovietnam.com offers a work permit application service that includes updating applicants on the latest regulations, determining eligibility for work permit exemption, minimizing the required documents, assisting with document preparation, ensuring document legality and logic, handling the application process with the Department of Labor, Invalids and Social Affairs, and updating applicants on the status of their application.<br />\r\nThe service offers assistance with a variety of work permit applications, including those for foreign managers, experts, technical workers, and English and yoga teachers, as well as work permit exemption certificates, extensions, and re-issuances.<br />\r\nTo apply for a work permit through Urgentvisatovietnam.com, applicants can contact the company for a free initial assessment and quote. After preparing and sending the necessary documents to the company, Urgentvisatovietnam.com will handle the application process with the relevant authorities until the work permit is issued. Once the work permit is available, applicants can pick it up at the company&#39;s office or have it sent to their physical address.<br />\r\nUrgentvisatovietnam.com offers over 05 years of experience in work permit application services, with no hidden charges and clear communication of costs in advance. The company also signs an agreement with applicants outlining the rights and obligations of each party and offers the convenience of support from anywhere in Vietnam.<br />\r\nThe company provides free consultation and support for those seeking work permits in Vietnam. Interested applicants can contact Urgentvisatovietnam.com with their contact details for further information and assistance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Obtaining a work permit in Vietnam can be a daunting task, but with the right information and guidance, it is possible to navigate the process successfully. In this article, we have provided a comprehensive guide to obtaining a work permit in Vietnam, including eligibility requirements, application procedures, common mistakes to avoid, and the benefits of using a work permit service provider.<br />\r\nIt is important to remember that obtaining a work permit is crucial for any foreigner seeking employment in Vietnam. Failure to obtain a work permit can result in fines, deportation, and other legal consequences. Therefore, it is essential to follow the correct procedures and ensure that all requirements are met.<br />\r\nIf you are planning to work in Vietnam as a foreigner, we hope that this guide has provided you with valuable information and guidance on how to obtain a work permit. With the right preparation and support, you can successfully obtain a work permit and enjoy the benefits of working and living in Vietnam.</p>\r\n', 'vietnam work permit-5.JPG', '0', 1, '', '2023-03-22', '2023-07-18', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Assistance in obtaining work permits for foreign individuals working in Vietnam', 'Vietnam has emerged as one of the most attractive destinations for foreign investors and professionals seeking new opportunities. However, the process of obtaining a work permit in Vietnam can be daunting, especially for those unfamiliar with the country\'s regulations and procedures', 'assistance-in-obtaining-work-permits-for-foreign-individuals-working-in-vietnam', 'vietnam work permit', 1, 1),
(74, 'Vietnam Temporary Residence Card Service: Everything You Need to Know', 'If you\'re planning to stay in Vietnam for an extended period of time, you may need a Vietnam temporary residence card (TRC). This card allows you to stay in Vietnam for longer than the standard tourist visa allows, and it can make your life in Vietnam much easier', '<p>If you&#39;re planning to stay in Vietnam for an extended period of time, you may need a temporary residence card (TRC). This card allows you to stay in Vietnam for longer than the standard tourist visa allows, and it can make your life in Vietnam much easier. In this article, we&#39;ll go over everything you need to know about the Vietnam temporary residence card service.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is a Temporary Residence Card?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A temporary residence card is a document issued by the Vietnamese government that allows foreign nationals to stay in Vietnam for longer than the standard tourist visa allows. The card is valid for a maximum of three years and can be renewed. With a temporary residence card, you can come and go from Vietnam without having to apply for a new visa each time.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Who is Eligible for a Temporary Residence Card?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Not everyone is eligible for a temporary residence card. To be eligible, you must fall into one of the following categories:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A foreigner who has a Vietnam work permit which is valid for at least 12 months at the time of applying for the temporary residence card.</li>\r\n	<li>Foreigners who are members of diplomatic missions, consular offices, representative offices of international organizations affiliated with the United Nations, intergovernmental organizations in Vietnam and their spouses, children under 18 years of age, and housemaids who are accompanied by the term of office, are granted temporary residence card with symbol NG3.</li>\r\n	<li>Foreigners who are granted LV1, LV2, ĐT, NN1, NN2, DH, PV1, LD, and TT visas are granted temporary residence cards with symbols similar to the visa symbols. The Law on Entry, Exit, Transit, and Residence of Foreigners in Vietnam 2014 has defined new types of symbols and the duration of each type of visa symbol for foreigners in Vietnam.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Requirements and conditions for a temporary residence card</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Foreigners must temporarily stay for 1 year or more in Vietnam</li>\r\n	<li>The passport is valid for at least 13 months.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to Apply for a Temporary Residence Card</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To apply for a temporary residence card, you must go through the following steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Obtain a sponsor: You must have a sponsor in Vietnam to apply for a temporary residence card. Your sponsor can be your employer, your school, or a Vietnamese national.</li>\r\n	<li>Prepare your documents: You will need to prepare the following documents:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Passport with a valid visa</li>\r\n		<li>Temporary residence registration form</li>\r\n		<li>Health certificate</li>\r\n		<li>Criminal record certificate</li>\r\n		<li>Four passport-sized photos</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Submit your application: You will need to submit your application to the Vietnam Immigration Department. The processing time can take up to 30 working days.</li>\r\n	<li>Collect your card: Once your application is approved, you can collect your temporary residence card at the immigration office.\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>44-46 Tran Phu, Ba Dinh, Hanoi.</li>\r\n		<li>254 Nguyen Trai, District 1, Ho Chi Minh City.</li>\r\n		<li>7 Tran Quy Cap, Da Nang City</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Cost of a Temporary Residence Card</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The cost of a temporary residence card varies depending on the length of the card and your nationality. As a general rule, the cost is as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>US $145/card valid for up to 2 years</li>\r\n	<li>US $155/card valid for over 2 years to up to 5 years</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Validity of Temporary Residence Card</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The validity of the temporary residence card in Vietnam is at least 30 days shorter than the remaining duration of the passport.</li>\r\n	<li>The temporary residence cards with the symbol ĐT1 are valid for no more than 10 years.</li>\r\n	<li>The temporary residence cards with the symbols NG3, LV1, LV2, LS, ĐT2 and DH are valid for no more than 05 years</li>\r\n	<li>The temporary residence cards with symbols NN1, NN2, ĐT3, and TT are valid for not more than 03 years.</li>\r\n	<li>The temporary residence cards with symbols LĐ1, LĐ2, and PV1 are valid for no more than 02 years.</li>\r\n	<li>Expired temporary resident cards are considered for issuing new ones.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Benefits of a Temporary Residence Card</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Having a temporary residence card can make your life in Vietnam much easier. Here are some of the benefits of having a temporary residence card:<br />\r\n<strong>1. To Change a Vietnam Temporary Residence Card</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Temporary residence card is lost</li>\r\n	<li>The temporary residence card is torn or with a fuzzy number</li>\r\n	<li>Foreigners are granted a new passport in which the new passport number is different from the passport number indicated on the temporary residence card</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. The validity of the renewed temporary residence card</strong><br />\r\nThe renewed temporary residence card duration will be equal to the period written on the previously issued temporary residence card.<br />\r\n<strong>3. To Extend Vietnam Temporary Residence Card</strong><br />\r\nForeigners can extend their temporary residence card in Vietnam upon its expiry</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What makes our Temporary Residence Card Service stand out?</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Our Vietnam temporary residence card service has been in operation since 2010 and we pride ourselves on our extensive knowledge of the requirements for foreigners seeking temporary residence in Vietnam. We highly recommend using our service because of the following reasons:</li>\r\n	<li>Expertise: Our team is highly knowledgeable in the legal regulations for obtaining a temporary residence card in Vietnam due to our long-standing experience in this field.</li>\r\n	<li>Convenience: Our service is designed to make obtaining a temporary residence card as convenient as possible for you. We assist in minimizing the number of documents required, saving you valuable time.</li>\r\n	<li>Guarantee: We provide timely updates on the progress of your application and ensure that results are delivered on time.</li>\r\n	<li>No hidden charges: We clearly communicate all costs associated with our temporary residence card service upfront, with no additional charges or hidden fees.</li>\r\n	<li>Responsibility: We will sign an agreement outlining the rights and obligations of both parties involved in the temporary residence card application process.</li>\r\n	<li>Regardless of your location, we urge you to reach out to us for expert advice on saving time and money, as well as improving your work efficiency.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents required to register TRC Vietnam with Urgentvisatovietnam.com</strong><br />\r\nThe following documents are required when applying for a Vietnam Temporary Residence Card through our service:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Passport: A copy of the passport pages containing the personal information and the latest Vietnamese visa.</li>\r\n	<li>Application form: The application form for a temporary residence card must be completed with accurate information and signed by the applicant.</li>\r\n	<li>Health certificate: A health certificate issued within the last six months from a recognized medical facility in Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>Criminal record: A criminal record issued by the applicant&#39;s home country or Vietnam&#39;s relevant agency, which should be legalized by the Vietnamese embassy in the home country or by the consular section of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs in Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>Work permit: A work permit is required for applicants who are working in Vietnam. The work permit should be valid for at least one year at the time of application.</li>\r\n	<li>Temporary residence registration: A temporary residence registration form that has been completed and certified by the applicant&#39;s local police department.</li>\r\n	<li>Photos: Two passport-sized photos (4cm x 6cm) with a white background.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>Note that additional documents may be required depending on the applicant&#39;s specific circumstances, such as a marriage certificate for applicants who are married to Vietnamese citizens or a birth certificate for applicants who were born in Vietnam. Our service will provide a detailed list of required documents and assist with the application process to ensure a smooth and successful outcome.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', 'vietnam temporary resident card-5.JPG', '0', 1, '', '2023-03-22', '2023-07-18', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Vietnam Temporary Residence Card Service: Everything You Need to Know', 'If you\'re planning to stay in Vietnam for an extended period of time, you may need a Vietnam temporary residence card (TRC). This card allows you to stay in Vietnam for longer than the standard tourist visa allows, and it can make your life in Vietnam much easier', 'vietnam-temporary-residence-card-service-everything-you-need-to-know', 'Vietnam temporary residence card', 1, 1),
