(82, 'Vietnam eVisa: How to obtain an Electronic Visa', 'The Vietnam eVisa serves as an electronic travel authorization, granting foreign travelers permission to visit Vietnam for tourism or business. Designed for single-entry use, this digital visa enables a stay of up to 30 days and more.', '<p>Vietnam is a beautiful country in Southeast Asia that has become a popular destination for tourists and business travelers alike. To enter Vietnam, foreign visitors must obtain a visa. While there are several types of visas available, the Vietnam eVisa has become a popular option for its convenience and simplicity. In this article, we will discuss everything you need to know about the Vietnam eVisa, including eligibility, application process, requirements, and more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is the Vietnam eVisa?</h2>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>The Vietnamese e-visa is a digital document, extending entry to Vietnam for a designated duration, accessible to citizens from 80 eligible countries. This convenient e-visa can be acquired through the government&#39;s official website via an online application. It allows for a one-time entry into Vietnam and permits a stay of up to 30 days within the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Update</strong>: Starting from August 15, 2023, a three-month multi-entry e-visa option will be made available.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>The Vietnam Electronic Visa, commonly known as the Vietnam E-visa, is one of the visa types issued by the Vietnam Immigration Department for foreign visitors entering the country. The E-visa is valid for single-entry use and allows a stay of up to 30 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unlike the traditional visa application process conducted at the Embassy and physically stamped onto the passport, the E-visa is processed electronically but holds the same legal value. Foreigners can easily apply for the E-visa through the official e-visa website, make the required payment, and await the outcome. The processing time typically takes 3 to 5 working days, and upon approval, applicants can print the visa directly from the system.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While the E-visa is suitable for various purposes, such as tourism, short business trips, and visiting family, it remains relatively new to citizens worldwide. Presently, Vietnam supports online visa issuance for citizens of 80 countries across the globe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>E-visa in brief</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Year of introduction</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>2017 (February)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Eligible countries</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>80 countries (initially 46)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Number of entry ports</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>33 (8 airports, 16 landports and 9 seaports)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Fee (gov&nbsp;fees)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>25 USD</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Processing time</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>3-5 working days</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Official website</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>https://immigration.gov.vn</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>This is the only official website, do not get misled by fake official websites.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>E-visa validity</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>30 days, single entry only</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Upcoming proposal</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Prolonged to 3 month (single/multiple entry)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Who is eligible for the Vietnam eVisa?</h2>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>As per the Vietnam Immigration Department, Vietnam has introduced a pilot program for E-visa issuance, extending this option to citizens from 80 countries. Under this program, foreigners can apply for the E-visa, which allows a maximum stay of 30 days. The E-visa is versatile, catering to different purposes such as sightseeing, participating in organized tours, conducting business trips (with sponsorship required), and visiting family.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>The E-visa is accessible to citizens of any of the 80 countries listed below.</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>Continent</th>\r\n			<th>Countries</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Europe</td>\r\n			<td>Andorra, Armenia, Austria, Azerbaijan, Belarus, Belgium, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Cyprus, Czech Republic, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Georgia, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Iceland, Ireland, Italy, Latvia, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Macedonia The former Yugoslav of, Malta, Moldova, Monaco, Montenegro, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Russia, San Marino, Serbia, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Asia</td>\r\n			<td>Brunei, China (including Hong Kong SAR and Macau SAR passport holders, but not Chinese e-passport holders), India, Japan, Kazakhstan, Korea (South), Mongolia, Myanmar, Nauru, Palau, Philippines, Qatar, Timor Leste, United Arab Emirates</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Oceania</td>\r\n			<td>Australia, Fiji, Marshall Islands, Micronesia Federated States of, Netherland, New Zealand, Papua New Guinea, Samoa, Solomon Islands, Vanuatu</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>North America</td>\r\n			<td>Canada, United States of America</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>South America</td>\r\n			<td>Argentina, Brazil, Chile, Colombia, Peru, Uruguay, Venezuela</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What are the requirements for the Vietnam eVisa?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible for the Vietnam eVisa, you must meet the following criteria:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Reside in a country other than Vietnam and not currently be present in Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>Possess a valid passport with at least 6 months of validity at the time of application.</li>\r\n	<li>Not be prohibited from entering Vietnam, as specified in Article 21 of the Law on entry, exit, transit, and residence of foreigners in Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>Hold citizenship in one of the countries listed as eligible for Vietnam&#39;s e-Visa under the provisions of Decree No. 7/2017/ND-CP issued by the Vietnam Government.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Additionally, it is crucial to provide accurate information on the application form that matches your passport details. Any inconsistencies may lead to the rejection of your application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What are the benefits of the Vietnam eVisa?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>E-visa offers remarkable advantages for international citizens, workers, investors, and more by streamlining the visa process and procedures.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Anywhere - anytime process: Instead of visiting an Embassy, you can apply for a visa from anywhere and at any time with just a computer or laptop connected to the Internet. The entire process is conducted online through the official E-visa website in Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>Simplified procedure: Unlike other visa methods that require numerous documents, the E-visa registration is straightforward. You only need to follow step-by-step instructions and provide the necessary information on the website.</li>\r\n	<li>Time and cost-saving: Avoid the hassle and expenses of traveling back and forth to the Vietnam Embassy. With E-visa, you can easily process your application from the comfort of your own home, saving time, money, and energy.</li>\r\n	<li>Easy follow-up: Your E-visa application will be associated with a registration code. After submission, you can effortlessly track and self-check the progress and result using this code with just a few clicks on your computer.</li>\r\n	<li>Convenience: Once you obtain an E-visa online, you can conveniently save the PDF file of your visa and print it yourself, making it readily available for your travels.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What are the limitations of the Vietnam eVisa</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>While the benefits of E-visa are substantial, there are some drawbacks associated with this new visa option:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Eligibility: E-visa is currently available for citizens of over 80 countries, but not all foreigners qualify for it. Before applying, you must verify if your country is on the eligible list.</li>\r\n	<li>Duration of stay: The Vietnam E-visa allows a stay of only 30 days. If you plan to stay longer, you&#39;ll need to opt for another type of visa.</li>\r\n	<li>Entry time: E-visa permits single-entry only. If you need to enter Vietnam multiple times for business or other purposes, this visa option is not suitable.</li>\r\n	<li>High accuracy requirement: The approval of the visa relies entirely on the information provided during the application process. If any information is incorrect or insufficient, you cannot amend it after submission. Moreover, the application fee is non-refundable if the application gets rejected.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>To avoid any visa-related issues during your trip to Vietnam, it is essential to plan accordingly. If your stay exceeds 30 days, explore alternative visa options, and ensure you acquire the necessary visas or permits if you plan to leave and re-enter Vietnam.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Tips for a successful Vietnam eVisa application</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To enhance the chances of a successful Vietnam eVisa application, follow these helpful tips:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Double-check all information: Ensure that all details provided in your application match your passport precisely, as any inconsistencies may lead to rejection.</li>\r\n	<li>Use a high-quality passport photo: Submit a clear and high-quality passport photo to facilitate a smooth application process.</li>\r\n	<li>Apply early: To allow sufficient processing time, apply for your eVisa at least one week before your intended travel date.</li>\r\n	<li>Check your email regularly: Your eVisa will be sent to your email, so regularly monitor your inbox and ensure that your email address is accurate on the application.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>In conclusion, the Vietnam eVisa presents a convenient and cost-effective option for travelers visiting Vietnam for tourism or business purposes. With a straightforward application process and swift processing time, obtaining an eVisa has become hassle-free. However, it is crucial to be mindful of the requirements and limitations to ensure a successful application and a seamless travel experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>To obtain a Vietnam eVisa, you can follow these steps:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. Preparation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To ensure a smooth and efficient application for an e-visa, you will need to submit the following documents and information:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A passport with at least six (6) months&#39; validity from the date of application.</li>\r\n	<li>A clear photo of your full passport data page in .jpg format, displaying your photo, personal information, and ICAO lines.</li>\r\n	<li>A portrait photo in .jpg format, sized 4x6, with a white background, facing straight, and without glasses.</li>\r\n	<li>A temporary residential address in Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>A valid international credit or debit card for the payment process.</li>\r\n	<li>Your intended date of entry and exit from Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>The specific port of entry and exit from the List of ports allowing e-Visa holders to enter and exit Vietnam (*).</li>\r\n	<li>A valid email address for the registration.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>By having these documents and details ready, you can expedite your e-visa application process and increase the likelihood of a successful application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. List of 33 ports allowing e-Visa holders to enter and exit Vietnam:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>Airports</th>\r\n			<th>Landports</th>\r\n			<th>Seaports</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>1. Cat Bi International Airport</td>\r\n			<td>9. Bo Y Landport</td>\r\n			<td>25. Chan May Seaport</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>2. Cam Ranh International Airport</td>\r\n			<td>10. Cha Lo Landport</td>\r\n			<td>26. Da Nang Seaport</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>3. Can Tho International Airport</td>\r\n			<td>11. Cau Treo Landport</td>\r\n			<td>27. Duong Dong Seaport</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>4. Da Nang International Airport</td>\r\n			<td>12. Huu Nghi Landport</td>\r\n			<td>28. Hon Gai Seaport</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>5. Noi Bai International Airport</td>\r\n			<td>13. Ha Tien Landport</td>\r\n			<td>29. Hai Phong Seaport</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>6. Phu Bai International Airport</td>\r\n			<td>14. Lao Bao Landport</td>\r\n			<td>30. Nha Trang Seaport</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>7. Phu Quoc International Airport</td>\r\n			<td>15. Lao Cai Landport</td>\r\n			<td>31. Quy Nhon Seaport</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>8. Tan Son Nhat International Air</td>\r\n			<td>16. La Lay Landport</td>\r\n			<td>32. Ho Chi Minh City Seaport</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>17. Moc Bai Landport</td>\r\n			<td>33. Vung Tau Seaport</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>18. Mong Cai Landport</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>19. Nam Can Landport</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>20. Na Meo Landport</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>21. Song Tien Landport</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>22. Tinh Bien Landport</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>23. Tay Trang Landport</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>24. Xa Mat Landport</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. Application</strong><br />\r\nAfter preparing all needed information and things, the process of E-visa application includes 3 steps below:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Step 1: Access the E-visa official website at https://immigration.gov.vn and fill up all required information including:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Photos of Passport data page and portrait photo as required</li>\r\n		<li>All personal information and information regarding your Vietnam stay</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>The registration code will be provided after Step 1. Save and keep it in a safe place for later check.</li>\r\n	<li>Step 2: Pay an E-visa fee of USD25. The processing time is 03 working days since your application is submitted.</li>\r\n	<li>Step 3: Access the official website again. From the E-visa search menu (https://immigration.gov.vn), enter registration code, registration email and date of birth to check the result. If your application is approved, you can print E-visa from the system to enter and exit Vietnam.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Processing times and fee</strong><br />\r\nThe processing time for a Vietnam E-visa is 03 working days since the Vietnam Immigration Department received your submission and full payment of the fee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The government application fee for E-visa is USD25. There are four payment methods available at the checkout gate, however, the most popular and convenient way is by a credit/debit card via a local payment processor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to apply evisa from Us?</h2>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><strong>Step 1</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4><strong>Before you apply</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Check your eligibility</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>E-visa is presently available to citizens from 80 countries only, please check if country is included in the <a href=\"/vietnam-evisa-eligible-countries\">list of eligible countires</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Photo requirement guidelines</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You need a recently taken photo of 4cm*6cm without glasses. Please see the <a href=\"/vietnam-visa-photo-instructions\">photo guidelines</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Applying on an expiring passport</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You need a valid passport for at least 6 months for this visa. If your passport is expiring soon, renew it before applying for an e-visa.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><strong>Step 2</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4><strong>Gather your documents</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Before proceeding with your e-visa application, ensure you have the following documents ready:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>A passport with a validity of at least six (06) months.</li>\r\n	<li>A scanned copy of your passport&#39;s full data (bio) page in .jpg format, clearly visible and legible.</li>\r\n	<li>A passport-sized photo in .jpg format (4x6cm) with a white background and without glasses.</li>\r\n	<li>A valid international credit or debit card for e-visa fee payment.</li>\r\n	<li>A temporary address in Vietnam (such as a hotel, homestay, or the address of your family/relatives).</li>\r\n	<li>Details of your intended entry and exit dates, along with the specific point of entry and exit from Vietnam&nbsp;(see <a href=\"/vietnam-evisa-ports-of-entry-and-checkpoints\">list of applicable ports</a>).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>By having these essential documents and details on hand, your e-visa application process will be smooth and straightforward.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><strong>Step 3</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4><strong>Apply for your E-visa</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Detailed guide for the e-visa application process:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Visit the our website for the application form: <a href=\"/step-1\">Apply Now</a></li>\r\n	<li>Submit .jpg images of your passport data page and passport photo.</li>\r\n	<li>Complete all necessary information from your passport data page. (Name, date of birth, nationality, passport number..ect)</li>\r\n	<li>Provide details regarding your trip. (Travel date, Inviting/ guaranteeing agency/ organization, place of stay, length of stay)</li>\r\n	<li>Pay the e-Visa fee (45 USD) through one of the available payment options. (Visa, master and other credit/debit cards)</li>\r\n	<li>Wait for 3-5 working days (Urgent processing is available upon request)</li>\r\n	<li>Check your e-visa document at the &quot;Evisa status&quot; page: <a href=\"/check-status\">Check Status</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><img alt=\"how to apply vietnam evisa\" height=\"304\" src=\"/image/images/How%20to%20apply%20vietnam%20evisa.png\" width=\"894\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"Vietnam evisa documents required\" height=\"476\" src=\"/image/images/vietnam%20evisa%20documents%20required.png\" width=\"890\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"Vietnam evisa checkpoints\" height=\"555\" src=\"/image/images/vietnam%20evisa%20checkpoints.png\" width=\"890\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The sample of&nbsp;Vietnam e-visa&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"sample of Vietnam evisa\" height=\"1119\" src=\"/image/images/Vietnam%20evisa%20sample.png\" width=\"890\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>If you require assistance with obtaining an e-visa service, we are available to help. Through our service, you will:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You won&#39;t need to personally fill out the application with the Vietnam Government as we will handle it for you. This ensures that you won&#39;t have to worry about providing incorrect information on your application form.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You won&#39;t need to monitor the status of your evisa processing as we will take care of it for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our Fees are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>\r\n			<p>Process Time</p>\r\n			</th>\r\n			<th>\r\n			<p>Fee (USD/Pax)</p>\r\n			</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>3 - 5 working days</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>$45</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>More details</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Hotline/WhatsApp: +84.904.879.729</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', 'vietnam evisa.png', '0', 1, '', '2023-03-23', '2023-08-04', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Vietnam eVisa: How to obtain an Electronic Visa', 'The Vietnam eVisa serves as an electronic travel authorization, granting foreign travelers permission to visit Vietnam for tourism or business. Designed for single-entry use, this digital visa enables a stay of up to 30 days and more.', 'vietnam-evisa-your-ultimate-guide-to-obtaining-an-electronic-visa', 'Vietnam eVisa', 1, 0),
(83, 'Vietnam Visa Requirements', 'There is a common, and short, checklist of what you need in order to apply for a Vietnam visa. This list applies for all passport-holders whose countries do not have visa exemption agreement with Vietnam. If you apply for special visa type (other than the tourist visa), additional documents may be required.', '', 'vietnam visa requirement.png', '0', 2, '', '2023-03-27', '2023-07-19', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Vietnam Visa Requirements', 'Check out essential Vietnam visa requirements for foreigners to Vietnam and documents required for visa application', 'vietnam-visa-requirements', 'vietnam visa requirements', 1, 0),
(85, 'Vietnam Visa Fees', 'Currently, the most cost-effective way to obtain a visa for Vietnam is through the e-visa application process. For a 30-day, single-entry visa, the current government fee is $25 USD.', '<blockquote>\r\n<p>Currently, the most cost-effective way to obtain a visa for Vietnam is through the e-visa application process. For a 30-day, single-entry visa, the current government fee is $25 USD.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vietnam e-visa fees</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you apply directly on the official government e-visa website, the fee is $25 USD for a 3-5 days processing time. This fee is non-refundable</li>\r\n	<li>If you would like to ensure a more guaranteed or timely delivery, you can apply on our website for an additional fee of 20&nbsp;USD/person. If your application is not processed on time or gets rejected, we will refund your fee in full.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<table id=\"tbTour\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>Processing time</th>\r\n			<th>1-pax</th>\r\n			<th>Stamping fee</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>3 - 5 working days</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>$45</td>\r\n			<td>$0</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>2 working days</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>$70</td>\r\n			<td>$0</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>1 working day</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>$95</td>\r\n			<td>$0</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Emergency</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\">\r\n			<p>☎ <a href=\"https://api.whatsapp.com/send?phone=+84904879729&amp;text=Hi%20UrgentVisaToVietnam!%20I%20am%20interested%20in%20your%20service.\">+84904879729</a></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>E-visa is presently available to citizens from 80 countries only, please check if country is included in the&nbsp;</em><a href=\"https://urgentvisatovietnam.cafelink.org/vietnam-evisa-eligible-countries\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, Times, \">list of eligible countires</a><em>.</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vietnam visa on arrival&nbsp;fees</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To get a Vietnam visa on arrival, you will need to pay two kinds of fees:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Service fee</strong> (also known as visa approval letter fee or application fee): to be paid online at the time of application to get visa application processed, your visa approval letter issued and delivered to your email.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Stamping fee</strong>: to be paid in cash to get Vietnam visa stamp on arrival at the airport</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<table id=\"tbTour\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>Type of visa</th>\r\n			<th>1-pax</th>\r\n			<th>Stamping fee</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Single 1 month</td>\r\n			<td>$80</td>\r\n			<td>$25</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Multiple 1 month</td>\r\n			<td>$80</td>\r\n			<td>$50</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', 'vietnam visa fee.png', '0', 2, '', '2023-03-28', '2023-07-19', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Vietnam Visa Fees', 'The Vietnam visa fee may vary depending on the way you opt to apply for your visa to Vietnam, as well as the visa type you wish to obtain', 'vietnam-visa-fees', 'Vietnam visa fee', 1, 0),
(86, 'Vietnam Visa Exemption', 'Vietnam visa exemption, also known as Vietnam visa waiver or Vietnam visa-free, allows foreign nationals to enter and stay in Vietnam for a specific period without the requirement of going through a visa application process', '<p>Vietnam visa exemption, also known as Vietnam visa waiver or Vietnam visa-free, allows foreign nationals to enter and stay in Vietnam for a specific period without the requirement of going through a visa application process. This exemption is made possible through bilateral or unilateral agreements between the Vietnamese government and the foreign national&#39;s country, facilitating hassle-free travel for eligible individuals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s essential to distinguish between this type of visa exemption and the Vietnam visa exemption certificate, commonly known as the <a href=\"https://urgentvisatovietnam.com/requirements-and-procedures-to-obtain-the-vietnam-5-year-visa-exemption\">Vietnam 5 years vis</a><a href=\"http://urgentvisatovietnam.com/requirements-and-procedures-to-obtain-the-vietnam-5-year-visa-exemption\">a</a>. While the former allows certain foreign nationals to enter Vietnam without a visa for a specific period, the latter is a separate document that grants a 5-year visa validity for specific eligible individuals. Both are distinct in their application and benefits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a simple exemption stamp as follows on their passport:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/image/images/vietnam%20exemption%20stamp.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vietnam Visa Exemption countries</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>s of January 2022, citizens holding regular passports from 25 countries are no longer required to obtain a visa to enter Vietnam. Here is the complete list of countries eligible for Vietnam visa exemption:</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>No.</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Country</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Maximum visa-free duration</strong></td>\r\n		