(92, 'Everything you need to know about the Vietnam Investor DT visa', 'Vietnam has been emerging as a promising destination for investors in recent years, thanks to its dynamic economy, strategic location, and favorable business climate. For foreign investors who wish to explore the Vietnamese market and seek new investment opportunities, the Investor DT visa is a crucial tool to facilitate their entry and stay in Vietnam', '<p>Vietnam has been emerging as a promising destination for investors in recent years, thanks to its dynamic economy, strategic location, and favorable business climate. For foreign investors who wish to explore the Vietnamese market and seek new investment opportunities, the Investor DT visa is a crucial tool to facilitate their entry and stay in Vietnam. In this article, we will delve into the details of the Vietnam Investor DT visa, including its benefits, requirements, and application process.<br />\r\nThe Vietnam Investor Visa is a type of visa designed for foreign investors who have invested or plan to invest in Vietnam. This visa allows investors to enter and stay in Vietnam for an extended period, providing them with ample time to explore the market and invest in their projects. The Investor Visa is a valuable tool for foreign investors who wish to explore and invest in Vietnam&#39;s promising market, and it offers several benefits, including long-term stay, multiple entries, and business flexibility.<br />\r\nTo obtain the Investor Visa, investors must meet specific investment requirements and fulfill other conditions, such as registering their business, obtaining a tax identification number, opening a bank account, and undergoing a health check. The application process typically involves submitting an application and supporting documents to the Vietnamese embassy or consulate in the investor&#39;s home country or country of residence, obtaining approval from the Ministry of Planning and Investment, and receiving the Investor Visa from the embassy or consulate. Overall, the Investor Visa is an essential tool for foreign investors looking to invest in Vietnam and is an excellent opportunity for them to explore Vietnam&#39;s potential market.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is the Investor DT visa?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Investor DT visa is a type of visa designed for foreign investors who have invested in Vietnam or intend to do so. This visa allows investors to enter and stay in Vietnam for up to five years, depending on the duration of their investment project. The Investor DT visa is an essential tool for foreign investors who wish to explore and invest in Vietnam&#39;s promising market.<br />\r\nThe Investor (DT) visa for Vietnam is a type of visa granted to foreign investors and foreign lawyers practicing in Vietnam, according to Law No. 47/2014/QH13 on foreigners&rsquo; entry into, exit from, transit through, and residence in Vietnam. However, the new Immigration Law No. 51/2019/QH14 amending and supplementing a number of articles of Law No. 47/2014/QH13 has categorized the Vietnam Investor visa into four types: DT1, DT2, DT3, and DT4.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>DT1 visa is granted to foreign investors and representatives of foreign organizations investing in Vietnam with a capital contribution of at least VND100 billion or investing in the business fields and areas of investment incentives decided by the Vietnam Government. This visa is valid for up to 5 years.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>DT2 visa is granted to foreign investors and representatives of foreign organizations investing in Vietnam with a capital contribution of VND50 &ndash; under VND100 billion or investing in the business fields of investment encouragement decided by the Vietnam Government. It is also valid for up to 5 years.</li>\r\n	<li>DT3 visa is granted to foreign investors and representatives of foreign organizations investing in Vietnam with a capital contribution of VND3 &ndash; under VND50 billion and is valid for up to 3 years.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>DT4 visa is granted to foreign investors and representatives of foreign organizations investing in Vietnam with a capital contribution of less than VND3 billion and is valid for up to 12 months.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Holders of an Investor visa to Vietnam can apply for a Vietnam temporary card that is valid for up to 10 years, sponsor their spouse/children to obtain a Vietnam TT visa if their visa is categorized as DT1, DT2, or DT3, and extend their visa following the instructions provided for visa extension.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Benefits of the Investor DT visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Investor DT visa offers several advantages for foreign investors, including:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Long-term stay: The Investor DT visa allows investors to stay in Vietnam for up to five years, providing them with ample time to explore the market and invest in their projects.</li>\r\n	<li>Multiple entries: The Investor DT visa permits multiple entries into Vietnam, enabling investors to enter and exit the country as many times as needed during their stay.</li>\r\n	<li>Business flexibility: The Investor DT visa allows investors to engage in a wide range of business activities, such as attending conferences, conducting market research, and negotiating deals.</li>\r\n	<li>Family sponsorship: The Investor DT visa allows investors to sponsor their family members to accompany them during their stay in Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>Fast processing: The Investor DT visa application process is relatively quick, with a typical processing time of around 7-10 working days.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Requirements for the Investor DT visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To obtain the Investor DT visa, foreign investors must meet the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Investment requirement: Investors must have invested or be planning to invest at least VND 3 billion in Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>Business registration: Investors must register their business in Vietnam and obtain a Business Registration Certificate (BRC).</li>\r\n	<li>Tax registration: Investors must register for tax and obtain a Tax Identification Number (TIN).</li>\r\n	<li>Bank account: Investors must open a bank account in Vietnam and provide evidence of their investment capital.</li>\r\n	<li>Criminal record: Investors must provide a criminal record from their home country or the country where they have resided for the last 6 months.</li>\r\n	<li>Health check: Investors must undergo a health check and provide a health certificate issued by a recognized medical facility.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>The application process for the Investor DT visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The application process for the Investor DT visa involves the following steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Submitting the application: Investors must submit their visa application and supporting documents to the Vietnamese embassy or consulate in their home country or country of residence.</li>\r\n	<li>Approval from the Ministry of Planning and Investment: Once the embassy or consulate receives the application, it will forward it to the Ministry of Planning and Investment for approval.</li>\r\n	<li>Visa issuance: After receiving approval from the Ministry of Planning and Investment, the embassy or consulate will issue the Investor DT visa to the applicant.</li>\r\n	<li>Visa extension: Investors can extend their Investor DT visa for up to five years, depending on the duration of their investment project.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to get an Investor Visa for Vietnam?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To obtain an Investor Visa for Vietnam, the procedure depends on whether you are applying for it in Vietnam or in a foreign country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1. Getting DT visa in Vietnam</strong><br />\r\nIf you are already in Vietnam and want to apply for a DT visa, you need to follow these steps:</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Step 1: Prepare the required documents:</strong><br />\r\nThe necessary documents to apply for an Investor Visa to Vietnam include:</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A certified copy of the Business Registration Certificate &amp; Investment Registration Certificate of the company you have invested in Vietnam (sponsor company).</li>\r\n	<li>A Certificate of Seal Specimen Registration or a notice on the publication of information about the sealed specimen of the sponsor company on the national enterprise registration portal.</li>\r\n	<li>Form NA16 &ndash; Registration form for the seal and signature of the legal representative of the sponsor company.</li>\r\n	<li>Form NA5 &ndash; Application for the visa, visa extension, and the extension of stay for foreigners in Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>Your original valid passport.</li>\r\n	<li>The Temporary Residence Registration Form, as required (see <a href=\"https://urgentvisatovietnam.com/vietnam-temporary-residence-card-service\">How to register temporary residence for foreigners in Vietnam</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Step 2: Submit the documents to the Immigration Department office of Vietnam</strong><br />\r\nYou or your agent must submit the required documents to the Office of the Vietnam Immigration Department in Hanoi, Ho Chi Minh City, Da Nang, or the Immigration Management sections of the police offices of the provinces/city where your company is located.</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Step 3: Receive the Vietnam Investor DT visa</strong><br />\r\nAfter submitting the documents, you will receive your Investor visa for Vietnam stamped on your passport in about five working days.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>2. If you are in your home country and wish to obtain a DT visa for Vietnam, you need to follow the steps mentioned below:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Step 1: Prepare documents for the Vietnam DT visa approval letter</strong><br />\r\nIn this case, you and the company in which you have invested should prepare the following documents:</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A certified copy of the Business Registration Certificate and Investment Registration of the sponsor company;</li>\r\n	<li>A Certificate of seal specimen registration or a notice on the publication of information on the sealed specimen of the sponsor company on the national enterprise registration portal;</li>\r\n	<li>Form NA16 &ndash; Registration form for the seal and signature of the legal representative of the sponsor company;</li>\r\n	<li>Form NA2 with Barcode &ndash; Request for pre-clearance of foreigners&rsquo; entry into Vietnam (complete here and print out).</li>\r\n	<li>A photo of the investor&#39;s passport.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Step 2: Submit documents for the Vietnam DT visa approval letter</strong><br />\r\nIn this step, your agent in Vietnam will submit the required documents prepared in step 1 to the office of the Vietnam Immigration Department in Hanoi, Ho Chi Minh City, or Da Nang.</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>After 5 working days, the agent will receive a visa approval letter, which serves as the basis for the foreign investor to obtain the DT visa stamp.</li>\r\n	<li>The agent will then send the scan of the visa approval letter to the investor&#39;s email.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Note: Your company can also ask a visa agent like Urgentvisatovietnam.com for assistance in these 2 steps. We will submit those documents to the Vietnam Immigration Department on their behalf and then send them the colored scan of your visa approval letter.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Step 3: Obtain the Vietnam DT Visa stamp</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The foreign investor will need to prepare the following documents to obtain the visa stamp for Vietnam entry:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>An original valid passport as prescribed by the law;</li>\r\n	<li>A printout of the Vietnam visa approval letter;</li>\r\n	<li>Two 4*6cm photos on white background</li>\r\n	<li>Vietnamese visa application form.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Depending on the location to pick up the DT visa stamp declared on Form NA2, the investor shall present themselves at the Vietnam Embassy/Consulate General or Vietnam arrival airport for a visa stamp. Then, they can enter Vietnam with a visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Get Vietnam Investor DT visa - Hassle-FREE</h2>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>05+ years of experience in Vietnam migration</li>\r\n	<li>24/7 support</li>\r\n	<li>Transparency in procedure and fees</li>\r\n	<li>Timely delivery guaranteed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em><strong>Disclaimers</strong>: That&#39;s all about how to obtain a DT visa for foreign investors in Vietnam. While we make an effort to ensure that the provided information is correct and up-to-date, there may be changes of which we are unaware.</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', 'vietnam investor visa-6.JPG', '0', 1, '', '2023-04-05', '2023-07-18', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Everything you need to know about the Vietnam Investor DT visa', 'Vietnam has been emerging as a promising destination for investors in recent years, thanks to its dynamic economy, strategic location, and favorable business climate. For foreign investors who wish to explore the Vietnamese market and seek new investment opportunities, the Investor DT visa is a crucial tool to facilitate their entry and stay in Vietnam', 'everything-you-need-to-know-about-the-vietnam-investor-dt-visa', 'Vietnam investor DT visa', 1, 0),
(93, 'Vietnam Work Visa: Everything You Need to Know', 'Vietnam is a popular destination for foreigners seeking employment opportunities in Southeast Asia. The country\'s rapid economic growth and relatively low cost of living make it an attractive option for those looking to live and work abroad. However, obtaining a Vietnam work visa can be a complex process, with various requirements and restrictions to navigate.', '<p>Vietnam is a popular destination for foreigners seeking employment opportunities in Southeast Asia. The country&#39;s rapid economic growth and relatively low cost of living make it an attractive option for those looking to live and work abroad. However, obtaining a Vietnam work visa can be a complex process, with various requirements and restrictions to navigate. In this article, we&#39;ll guide you through everything you need to know about Vietnam work visas, including types of visas, eligibility criteria, and application procedures.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Types of Vietnam Work Visas</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are several types of Vietnam work visas, each with its own eligibility criteria and application requirements. The most common types of work visas are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Work Permit (WP): A work permit is a document issued by the Department of Labor, Invalids and Social Affairs (DoLISA) that allows foreign nationals to legally work in Vietnam for a specific employer and for a limited period.</li>\r\n	<li>Temporary Residence Card (TRC): A temporary residence card is a document issued by the Immigration Department that allows foreign nationals to reside and work in Vietnam for an extended period, usually up to two years.</li>\r\n	<li>Business Visa (BV): A business visa is a type of visa that allows foreign nationals to enter Vietnam for business purposes, such as attending meetings or negotiating contracts. This type of visa does not allow for employment in Vietnam, but it can be a useful option for those seeking short-term business opportunities in the country.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Eligibility Criteria for Vietnam Work Visas</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible for a Vietnam work visa, foreign nationals must meet certain criteria, including:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Having a valid passport with at least six months of validity remaining.</li>\r\n	<li>Having a job offer from a Vietnamese employer.</li>\r\n	<li>Meeting the qualifications and experience requirements for the job.</li>\r\n	<li>Passing a medical examination and obtaining a health certificate.</li>\r\n	<li>Obtaining a police clearance certificate from their home country.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Application Procedures for Vietnam Work Visas</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The application procedures for Vietnam work visas can vary depending on the type of visa and the applicant&#39;s nationality. Generally, the application process involves the following steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Obtaining a job offer from a Vietnamese employer.</li>\r\n	<li>Applying for a work permit or temporary residence card from the DoLISA or Immigration Department.</li>\r\n	<li>Obtaining a visa approval letter from the Vietnam Immigration Department.</li>\r\n	<li>Applying for a visa at a Vietnamese embassy or consulate in the applicant&#39;s home country.</li>\r\n	<li>Arriving in Vietnam and completing the visa stamping process at the airport.</li>\r\n	<li>It&#39;s important to note that the application process can be time-consuming and may require the assistance of a professional immigration agent or lawyer.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to Get a Vietnam Work Visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;re planning to work in Vietnam, you&#39;ll need a valid work visa. The process of obtaining a Vietnam work visa can be a bit complicated, but it&#39;s not impossible. In this article, we&#39;ll provide a step-by-step guide on how to get a Vietnam work visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Step 1: Determine Your Visa Type</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The first step in obtaining a Vietnam work visa is to determine the type of visa that you need. The most common types of Vietnam work visas are the work permit and the temporary residence card. The work permit is a document issued by the Department of Labor, Invalids, and Social Affairs (DoLISA) that allows foreign nationals to legally work in Vietnam for a specific employer and for a limited period. The temporary residence card is a document issued by the Immigration Department that allows foreign nationals to reside and work in Vietnam for an extended period, usually up to two years.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Step 2: Find a Job in Vietnam</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>To obtain a Vietnam work visa, you&#39;ll need a job offer from a Vietnamese employer. It&#39;s important to find a reputable employer that is willing to sponsor your visa and that can provide you with a work permit or temporary residence card.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Step 3: Prepare Your Documents</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you have a job offer, you&#39;ll need to prepare your documents. You&#39;ll need a valid passport with at least six months of validity remaining, a police clearance certificate from your home country, and a health certificate. You&#39;ll also need to meet the qualifications and experience requirements for the job.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Step 4: Apply for a Work Permit or Temporary Residence Card</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>To apply for a work permit or temporary residence card, you&#39;ll need to submit your documents to the DoLISA or Immigration Department. The application process can be time-consuming and may require the assistance of a professional immigration agent or lawyer.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Step 5: Obtain a Visa Approval Letter</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Once your work permit or temporary residence card is approved, you&#39;ll need to obtain a visa approval letter from the Vietnam Immigration Department. This letter will allow you to apply for a visa at a Vietnamese embassy or consulate in your home country.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Step 6: Apply for a Visa</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>You&#39;ll need to apply for a visa at a Vietnamese embassy or consulate in your home country. You&#39;ll need to provide your passport, visa approval letter, and other required documents. The embassy or consulate will issue you a visa, which will allow you to enter Vietnam.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Step 7: Complete the Visa Stamping Process</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>When you arrive in Vietnam, you&#39;ll need to complete the visa stamping process at the airport. This involves presenting your visa and passport to the immigration officer, who will stamp your passport with the entry stamp.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How long does it take to get a Vietnam Work Visa?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The length of time it takes to obtain a work visa for Vietnam can vary depending on several factors, such as the type of visa, the processing time of the government agency, and the completeness and accuracy of the documents submitted. However, in general, the process can take several weeks to a few months. For a work permit, the processing time typically takes around 15 working days from the date of submission of the application, but it can take longer in some cases. The employer may need to obtain approval from various authorities, such as the Department of Labor, Invalids, and Social Affairs (DoLISA), the Ministry of Labor, Invalids, and Social Affairs (MOLISA), and the People&#39;s Committee in the province where the company is located. For a temporary residence card, the processing time can take around 5-7 working days from the date of submission of the application. However, the actual processing time can vary depending on the workload of the Immigration Department. It&#39;s important to note that the process can be delayed if there are any issues with the submitted documents or if additional documents are required. It&#39;s recommended to consult with a professional immigration agent or lawyer to ensure that all the required documents are complete and accurate before submitting the application. Overall, it&#39;s best to plan ahead and apply for a work visa well in advance of your intended travel date to allow for any potential delays in the process.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Difference between Vietnam Work Visa and Vietnam Business Visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Vietnam offers different types of visas for foreign nationals, including work visas and business visas. While both visas allow foreign nationals to enter Vietnam for employment or business purposes, there are significant differences between them in terms of eligibility, duration, and application requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>\r\n			<p>Vietnam Work Visa</p>\r\n			</th>\r\n			<th>\r\n			<p>Vietnam Busines Visa</p>\r\n			</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>A Vietnam work visa, also known as a work permit, is a document issued by the Vietnamese government that allows foreign nationals to legally work in Vietnam for a specific employer and for a limited period. To be eligible for a work visa, the applicant must have a job offer from a Vietnamese employer and meet the qualifications and experience requirements for the job. The employer must also obtain approval from various authorities, such as the Department of Labor, Invalids, and Social Affairs (DoLISA), the Ministry of Labor, Invalids, and Social Affairs (MOLISA), and the People&#39;s Committee in the province where the company is located. Work visas are typically valid for one year and can be extended upon expiry.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>A Vietnam business visa, also known as a business visa, is a document issued by the Vietnamese government that allows foreign nationals to enter Vietnam for business purposes, such as attending conferences, meetings, or trade fairs, or exploring business opportunities. Business visas do not allow the holder to work in Vietnam or receive payment from a Vietnamese company. Business visas are typically valid for one to three months and can be extended upon expiry.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>Application Requirements</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To apply for a work visa, the applicant must have a job offer from a Vietnamese employer and meet the qualifications and experience requirements for the job. The employer must also obtain approval from various authorities, such as the Department of Labor, Invalids, and Social Affairs (DoLISA), the Ministry of Labor, Invalids, and Social Affairs (MOLISA), and the People&#39;s Committee in the province where the company is located. The applicant must also provide a valid passport with at least six months of validity remaining, a police clearance certificate from their home country, and a health certificate. To apply for a business visa, the applicant must provide a valid passport with at least six months of validity remaining, a completed visa application form, and a letter of invitation from a Vietnamese company or organization. The letter of invitation must specify the purpose of the visit, the intended duration of stay, and the company&#39;s contact information. In summary, a Vietnam work visa allows foreign nationals to work legally in Vietnam for a specific employer, while a Vietnam business visa allows foreign nationals to enter Vietnam for business purposes. Both visas have different eligibility criteria, duration, and application requirements. It&#39;s important to carefully review the requirements and restrictions of each visa before applying. If you&#39;re unsure which visa to apply for, it&#39;s recommended to consult with a professional immigration agent or lawyer.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Obtaining a Vietnam work visa can be a complex process, but with the right information and guidance, it&#39;s possible to navigate the requirements and restrictions successfully. It&#39;s important to do your research and ensure that you meet all the eligibility criteria before applying for a visa. If you&#39;re considering working in Vietnam, we recommend consulting with an immigration agent or lawyer to help you through the application process and ensure that you&#39;re meeting all the necessary requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No matter you wish to obtain a business visa or a working visa, feel free to let us know via sale@urgentvisatovietnam.com</p>\r\n', 'vietnam work permit-5.JPG', '0', 1, '', '2023-04-10', '2023-07-19', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Vietnam Work Visa: Everything You Need to Know', 'Vietnam is a popular destination for foreigners seeking employment opportunities in Southeast Asia. The country\'s rapid economic growth and relatively low cost of living make it an attractive option for those looking to live and work abroad. However, obtaining a Vietnam work visa can be a complex process, with various requirements and restrictions to navigate.', 'vietnam-work-visa-everything-you-need-to-know', 'vietnam work visa', 1, 0),
(94, 'All the information you need to know about Vietnam visa extension and renewal', 'If you\'re planning a trip to Vietnam, you\'ll need a valid visa to enter the country. But what if you want to stay longer than your visa allows? Fortunately, there are options for extending or renewing your Vietnam visa', '<p>If you&#39;re planning a trip to Vietnam, you&#39;ll need a valid visa to enter the country. But what if you want to stay longer than your visa allows? Fortunately, there are options for extending or renewing your Vietnam visa. In this article, we&#39;ll cover everything you need to know about Vietnam visa extension and renewal.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Types of Vietnam Visas</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Before we dive into the details of visa extension and renewal, let&#39;s review the different types of visas available for Vietnam:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tourist Visa: This type of visa is suitable for those who plan to visit Vietnam for tourism purposes. It&#39;s valid for up to 3 months, and you can extend it for an additional 3 months.</li>\r\n	<li>Business Visa: This type of visa is for those who want to conduct business in Vietnam. It&#39;s also valid for up to 3 months, and you can extend it for an additional 3 months.</li>\r\n	<li>Work Visa: This type of visa is for those who plan to work in Vietnam. It&#39;s valid for up to 1 year, and you can extend it for an additional 3 years.</li>\r\n	<li>Student Visa: This type of visa is for those who plan to study in Vietnam. It&#39;s valid for the duration of your studies, and you can extend it as needed.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Now that you know the different types of visas available, let&#39;s explore the options for extending or renewing your Vietnam visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vietnam Visa Extension</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Applying for a visa extension is a process that enables foreigners to extend their stay in Vietnam without the need to exit the country. Once approved, an extension stamp will be added to their passport, indicating their new authorized stay duration. It&#39;s worth noting that a visa extension is only valid for single entry purposes.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vietnam Visa Renewal</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Visa renewal and visa extension share similarities as both options enable foreigners to extend their stay in Vietnam without the requirement to leave the country.<br />\r\nIn contrast to visa extension, visa renewal involves obtaining a new visa sticker and stay duration stamp on the passport, reflecting the updated duration permission. As a result, the visa renewal fee is typically higher than the visa extension fee, as it includes both the stamping fee and visa sticker fee.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Visa Extension/Renewal Requirements</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To extend/review your Vietnam visa, your original passport must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Be valid for at least 06 months from the time of extension/renewal.</li>\r\n	<li>Have at least 02 blank pages.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>What are the reasons to opt for a visa extension?</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The only choice is to continue remaining in Vietnam legally after your visa expiry date without leaving the country</li>\r\n	<li>Save your cost as the extension fee is much cheaper than the renewal fee.</li>\r\n	<li>Avoid being taken into the blacklist of the Vietnam Immigration Department because of overstaying.</li>\r\n	<li>Have more time to settle your business in Vietnam which might be interrupted if you leave Vietnam and then come back with a new visa.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Where to Extend Visa in Vietnam?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Hanoi immigration office: 44-46 Tran Phu, Ba Dinh District, Hanoi<br />\r\nImmigration office in Da Nang: 78 Le Loi, Thach Thang, Hai Chau, Da Nang<br />\r\nImmigration office in Ho Chi Minh City: 196 Nguyen Thi Minh Khai, Ward 6, District 3, Ho Chi Minh city<br />\r\nWorking hours: Monday-Friday (Morning: 7am &ndash; 11h30am; Afternoon: 1h30pm &ndash; 5pm) and Saturday (Morning time only)</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to extend Vietnam visa?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two options for obtaining a visa extension: applying directly at the Vietnam Immigration Department, or utilizing our Vietnam visa extension service for a more convenient process.<br />\r\nIf you choose to utilize our<a href=\"/all-the-information-you-need-to-know-about-vietnam-visa-extension-and-renewal\"> visa extension service</a>, the process of successfully extending your visa can be achieved in just three simple steps.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Step 1</strong>: Send us a soft copy of your passport and the page containing your current Vietnam visa and we will inform you whether your visa can be extended or not</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Step 2</strong>: Send your original passport to our address and pay the extension fee</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Step 3</strong>: Get your passport with extended stay within 8 working days normally or 3 working days in urgent case upon your request</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vietnam Visa Extension Cost and Duration</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The visa extension in Vietnam can be applied for the types of visas below:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Extend original visa exemption for up to 1 month</li>\r\n	<li>Extend original 1-month tourist visa for 1 month</li>\r\n	<li>Extend the original 1-month business visa for up to 3 months</li>\r\n	<li>Extend original 3 months tourist visa for 1 month;</li>\r\n	<li>Extend the original 3 months business visa for up to 3 months</li>\r\n	<li>Extend the original 5 years visa exemption certificate for up to 6 months</li>\r\n	<li>Extend original e-visa for up to 3 months</li>\r\n	<li>Extend 1-year tourist visa for US passport holders (tourist/business) for 1 month</li>\r\n	<li>Extend 1-year business visa for US passport holders for up to 3 months</li>\r\n	<li>Extend the temporary stay of APEC Business Travel Card holders for up to 3 months</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em><strong>Disclaimers:</strong> </em>Despite our efforts to maintain accurate and current information, it is possible that there might be changes of which we are unaware.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', 'vietnam visa extension-6.JPG', '0', 1, '', '2023-04-10', '2023-08-04', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'All the information you need to know about Vietnam visa extension and renewal', 'If you\'re planning a trip to Vietnam, you\'ll need a valid visa to enter the country. But what if you want to stay longer than your visa allows? Fortunately, there are options for extending or renewing your Vietnam visa', 'all-the-information-you-need-to-know-about-vietnam-visa-extension-and-renewal', ' Vietnam visa extension, Vietnam visa renewal', 1, 1),
(95, 'Vietnam Exit Visa', 'The majority of travelers typically obtain a standard Vietnam visa, which permits them to enter and exit the country. However, an exit visa serves a distinct purpose and is granted solely for the purpose of legally exiting Vietnam. So, who requires a Vietnam exit visa and how can one obtain it? To address these queries and related concerns, let us delve deeper into each section of this article.', '<p>The majority of travelers typically obtain a standard Vietnam visa, which permits them to enter and exit the country. However, an exit visa serves a distinct purpose and is granted solely for the purpose of legally exiting Vietnam. So, who requires a Vietnam exit visa and how can one obtain it? To address these queries and related concerns, let us delve deeper into each section of this article.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What&#39;s a Vietnam exit visa?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Immigration Office of Vietnam issues a Vietnam exit visa, which is a legitimate document that permits travelers to legally leave the country in the event of a lost or damaged passport, or an invalid visa. It is important to note that without obtaining an exit visa, leaving Vietnam legally is not possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Who needs a Vietnam exit visa?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A Vietnam exit visa&nbsp;is granted to foreign passport holders, which includes:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Infants with foreign passports who were born in Vietnam.&nbsp;When giving birth while residing in Vietnam, it is highly likely that your child does not possess a Vietnam visa in their passport. Therefore, in order to leave Vietnam legally, parents must obtain a birth certificate, passport, and exit visa for their child prior to departure.</li>\r\n	<li>Foreign visitors who lose their passports while staying in Vietnam.&nbsp;If you are faced with such circumstances, obtaining an exit visa after renewing your passport is crucial to legally depart from Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>Travelers who exceed their visa validity while staying in Vietnam.&nbsp;Deliberately or unintentionally overstaying in Vietnam can result in significant trouble with Vietnam Immigration while attempting to exit the country through any means. Obtaining an exit visa is strongly advised if one wishes to avoid severe consequences depending on the length of their overstay in Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>Foreign workers whose temporary resident card is confiscated by their employer following the termination of their labor contract.&nbsp;In practice, when employed by a company in Vietnam, a foreign worker is typically granted a resident card by the Vietnam Immigration Office with the sponsorship of the company. Therefore, when the employment contract terminates, the resident card is either canceled or retrieved by the company at the request of the Immigration Office. Consequently, the foreign worker no longer has a valid Vietnam Resident Card/Visa to continue staying and working in Vietnam unless they are employed by another company.&nbsp;In this case, you must inquire the sponsored company to submit an exit Vietnam visa at the Immigration Office of Vietnam so that he/she can leave Vietnam with a visa legitimately.</li>\r\n	<li>Foreigners who obtain new passports issued within Vietnam.&nbsp;In numerous cases, foreign travelers enter Vietnam with a valid Vietnam visa, but during their stay in the country, they need to obtain a new passport due to the expiration of their current passport with no additional pages for visas.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to apply for a Vietnam exit visa?</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Infants born in Vietnam hold foreign passports.</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Document required:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Child&rsquo;s original passport&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Birth certificate/ Notice of birth from the hospital</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Parent(s)&rsquo;s original passport&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steps</strong>: You can seek the assistance of any visa agency in Vietnam to obtain a Vietnam exit visa. They will submit a request for the visa on your behalf to the Vietnam Immigration Office.&nbsp;If you prefer to handle the process on your own, it is recommended that you visit the Vietnam Immigration Department directly.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Foreign visitors whose passports are lost or damaged during their stay in Vietnam.</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Visit the nearest ward police office to report your situation.</li>\r\n	<li>Visit your embassy/ consulate in Vietnam to apply for a new passport, emergency passport, or travel document.</li>\r\n	<li>Get in touch with a visa agency to help you submit your exit visa application.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Get a visa stick on your passport after 5-7 working days</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Travelers who exceed their visa validity during their stay in Vietnam.</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Required documents:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Original passport with the expired Vietnam visa</li>\r\n	<li>A detailed letter explaining the reason for overstaying</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of departure flight, indicating the date you plan to leave Vietnam.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steps</strong>: Immediately contact a visa agency to handle your overstaying <strong>&gt;&gt;</strong> Submit your original passport <strong>&gt;&gt;</strong> Pay a fine for overstaying and exit visa fee <strong>&gt;&gt;&nbsp;</strong>Get your exit visa stamped on your passport and prepare to exit Vietnam</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Travelers who exceed their visa validity during their stay in Vietnam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Required documents:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Original passport with the expired Vietnam visa</li>\r\n	<li>A detailed letter explaining the reason for overstaying</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of departure flight, indicating the date you plan to leave Vietnam.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steps</strong>: Immediately contact a visa agency to handle your overstaying <strong>&gt;&gt;</strong> Submit your original passport <strong>&gt;&gt;</strong> Pay a fine for overstaying and exit visa fee <strong>&gt;&gt;</strong> Get your exit visa stamped on your passport and prepare to exit Vietnam</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Foreign workers whose temporary resident card is collected upon termination of their work contract.</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steps</strong>: Submit your temporary resident card with your original passport <strong>&gt;&gt;</strong> Prepare documents signed and stamped by your company (Included the letter explaining the cancellation/withdrawal of residence card) <strong>&gt;&gt;</strong> Pay the processing fee <strong>&gt;&gt;</strong> Receive the visa stamped on your passport between 5 and 7 working days</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Foreigners who have renewed/issued their new passports in Vietnam.</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Required documents:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your old passport</li>\r\n	<li>Your new passport</li>\r\n	<li>Processing fee</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have renewed or obtained a new passport while your visa is still valid in the old one, you can transfer your visa to the new passport. The new visa sticker on the new passport will have the same validity as the one on the old passport. It is important to note that both old and new passports must be submitted together for the transfer process.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vietnam exit visa cost</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The fee for an exit Vietnam visa may vary depending on the nationality and situation of the applicant. Generally, the cost of an exit visa is around $100 US. The purpose of an exit visa is to allow you to leave Vietnam, so its duration is limited. Typically, it lasts for 10-15 days, which should be enough time for you to plan your departure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After submitting all the required documents, it takes about 5-7 working days to obtain the exit visa from the Vietnam Immigration Department.</p>\r\n', 'vietnam exit visa photo.JPG', '0', 1, '', '2023-04-17', '2023-07-18', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Vietnam Exit Visa', 'The majority of travelers typically obtain a standard Vietnam visa, which permits them to enter and exit the country. However, an exit visa serves a distinct purpose and is granted solely for the purpose of legally exiting Vietnam. So, who requires a Vietnam exit visa and how can one obtain it? To address these queries and related concerns, let us delve deeper into each section of this article.', 'vietnam-exit-visa', 'Vietnam exit visa', 1, 0),
