(127, 'vn', 'Vietnam Visa Exemption', 'Vietnam visa exemption, also known as Vietnam visa waiver or Vietnam visa-free, allows foreign nationals to enter and stay in Vietnam for a specific period without the requirement of going through a visa application process', '<p>Vietnam visa exemption, also known as Vietnam visa waiver or Vietnam visa-free, allows foreign nationals to enter and stay in Vietnam for a specific period without the requirement of going through a visa application process. This exemption is made possible through bilateral or unilateral agreements between the Vietnamese government and the foreign national&#39;s country, facilitating hassle-free travel for eligible individuals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s essential to distinguish between this type of visa exemption and the Vietnam visa exemption certificate, commonly known as the <a href=\"https://urgentvisatovietnam.com/requirements-and-procedures-to-obtain-the-vietnam-5-year-visa-exemption\">Vietnam 5 years vis</a><a href=\"http://urgentvisatovietnam.com/requirements-and-procedures-to-obtain-the-vietnam-5-year-visa-exemption\">a</a>. While the former allows certain foreign nationals to enter Vietnam without a visa for a specific period, the latter is a separate document that grants a 5-year visa validity for specific eligible individuals. Both are distinct in their application and benefits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a simple exemption stamp as follows on their passport:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/image/images/vietnam%20exemption%20stamp.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vietnam Visa Exemption countries</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>s of January 2022, citizens holding regular passports from 25 countries are no longer required to obtain a visa to enter Vietnam. Here is the complete list of countries eligible for Vietnam visa exemption:</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>No.</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Country</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Maximum visa-free duration</strong></td