(139, 'vn', 'Everything you need to know about the Vietnam Investor DT visa', 'Vietnam has been emerging as a promising destination for investors in recent years, thanks to its dynamic economy, strategic location, and favorable business climate. For foreign investors who wish to explore the Vietnamese market and seek new investment opportunities, the Investor DT visa is a crucial tool to facilitate their entry and stay in Vietnam', '<p>Vietnam has been emerging as a promising destination for investors in recent years, thanks to its dynamic economy, strategic location, and favorable business climate. For foreign investors who wish to explore the Vietnamese market and seek new investment opportunities, the Investor DT visa is a crucial tool to facilitate their entry and stay in Vietnam. In this article, we will delve into the details of the Vietnam Investor DT visa, including its benefits, requirements, and application process.<br />\r\nThe Vietnam Investor Visa is a type of visa designed for foreign investors who have invested or plan to invest in Vietnam. This visa allows investors to enter and stay in Vietnam for an extended period, providing them with ample time to explore the market and invest in their projects. The Investor Visa is a valuable tool for foreign investors who wish to explore and invest in Vietnam&#39;s promising market, and it offers several benefits, including long-term stay, multiple entries, and business flexibility.<br />\r\nTo obtain the Investor Visa, investors must meet specific investment requirements and fulfill other conditions, such as registering their business, obtaining a tax identification number, opening a bank account, and undergoing a health check. The application process typically involves submitting an application and supporting documents to the Vietnamese embassy or consulate in the investor&#39;s home country or country of residence, obtaining approval from the Ministry of Planning and Investment, and receiving the Investor Visa from the embassy or consulate. Overall, the Investor Visa is an essential tool for foreign investors looking to invest in Vietnam and is an excellent opportunity for them to explore Vietnam&#39;s potential market.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is the Investor DT visa?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Investor DT visa is a type of visa designed for foreign investors who have invested in Vietnam or intend to do so. This visa allows investors to enter and stay in Vietnam for up to five years, depending on the duration of their investment project. The Investor DT visa is an essential tool for foreign investors who wish to explore and invest in Vietnam&#39;s promising market.<br />\r\nThe Investor (DT) visa for Vietnam is a type of visa granted to foreign investors and foreign lawyers practicing in Vietnam, according to Law No. 47/2014/QH13 on foreigners&rsquo; entry into, exit from, transit through, and residence in Vietnam. However, the new Immigration Law No. 51/2019/QH14 amending and supplementing a number of articles of Law No. 47/2014/QH13 has categorized the Vietnam Investor visa into four types: DT1, DT2, DT3, and DT4.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>DT1 visa is granted to foreign investors and representatives of foreign organizations investing in Vietnam with a capital contribution of at least VND100 billion or investing in the business fields and areas of investment incentives decided by the Vietnam Government. This visa is valid for up to 5 years.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>DT2 visa is granted to foreign investors and representatives of foreign organizations investing in Vietnam with a capital contribution of VND50 &ndash; under VND100 billion or investing in the business fields of investment encouragement decided by the Vietnam Government. It is also valid for up to 5 years.</li>\r\n	<li>DT3 visa is granted to foreign investors and representatives of foreign organizations investing in Vietnam with a capital contribution of VND3 &ndash; under VND50 billion and is valid for up to 3 years.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>DT4 visa is granted to foreign investors and representatives of foreign organizations investing in Vietnam with a capital contribution of less than VND3 billion and is valid for up to 12 months.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Holders of an Investor visa to Vietnam can apply for a Vietnam temporary card that is valid for up to 10 years, sponsor their spouse/children to obtain a Vietnam TT visa if their visa is categorized as DT1, DT2, or DT3, and extend their visa following the instructions provided for visa extension.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Benefits of the Investor DT visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Investor DT visa offers several advantages for foreign investors, including:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Long-term stay: The Investor DT visa allows investors to stay in Vietnam for up to five years, providing them with ample time to explore the market and invest in their projects.</li>\r\n	<li>Multiple entries: The Investor DT visa permits multiple entries into Vietnam, enabling investors to enter and exit the country as many times as needed during their stay.</li>\r\n	<li>Business flexibility: The Investor DT visa allows investors to engage in a wide range of business activities, such as attending conferences, conducting market research, and negotiating deals.</li>\r\n	<li>Family sponsorship: The Investor DT visa allows investors to sponsor their family members to accompany them during their stay in Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>Fast processing: The Investor DT visa application process is relatively quick, with a typical processing time of around 7-10 working days.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Requirements for the Investor DT visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To obtain the Investor DT visa, foreign investors must meet the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Investment requirement: Investors must have invested or be planning to invest at least VND 3 billion in Vietnam.</li>\r\n	<li>Business registration: Investors must register their business in Vietnam and obtain a Business Registration Certificate (BRC).</li>\r\n	<li>Tax registration: Investors must register for tax and obtain a Tax Identification Number (TIN).</li>\r\n	<li>Bank account: Investors must open a bank account in Vietnam and provide evidence of their investment capital.</li>\r\n	<li>Criminal record: Investors must provide a criminal record from their home country or the country where they have resided for the last 6 months.</li>\r\n	<li>Health check: Investors must undergo a health check and provide a health certificate issued by a recognized medical facility.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>The application process for the Investor DT visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The application process for the Investor DT visa involves the following steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Submitting the application: Investors must submit their visa application and supporting documents to the Vietnamese embassy or consulate in their home country or country of residence.</li>\r\n	<li>Approval from the Ministry of Planning and Investment: Once the embassy or consulate receives the application, it will forward it to the Ministry of Planning and Investment for approval.</li>\r\n	<li>Visa issuance: After receiving approval from the Ministry of Planning and Investment, the embassy or consulate will issue the Investor DT visa to the applicant.</li>\r\n	<li>Visa extension: Investors can extend their Investor DT visa for up to five years, depending on the duration of their investment project.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to get an Investor Visa for Vietnam?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To obtain an Investor Visa for Vietnam, the procedure depends on whether you are applying for it in Vietnam or in a foreign country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1. Getting DT visa in Vietnam</strong><br />\r\nIf you are already in Vietnam and want to apply for a DT visa, you need to follow these steps:</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Step 1: Prepare the required documents:</strong><br />\r\nThe necessary documents to apply for an Investor Visa to Vietnam include:</h4>\r\