 a work visa well in advance of your intended travel date to allow for any potential delays in the process.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Difference between Vietnam Work Visa and Vietnam Business Visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Vietnam offers different types of visas for foreign nationals, including work visas and business visas. While both visas allow foreign nationals to enter Vietnam for employment or business purposes, there are significant differences between them in terms of eligibility, duration, and application requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;Vietnam Work Visa</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;Vietnam Busines Visa</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>A Vietnam work visa, also known as a work permit, is a document issued by the Vietnamese government that allows foreign nationals to legally work in Vietnam for a specific employer and for a limited period. To be eligible for a work visa, the applicant must have a job offer from a Vietnamese employer and meet the qualifications and experience requirements for the job. The employer must also obtain approval from various authorities, such as the Department of Labor, Invalids, and Social Affairs (DoLISA), the Ministry of Labor, Invalids, and Social Affairs (MOLISA), and the People&#39;s Committee in the province where the company is located. Work visas are typically valid for one year and can be extended upon expiry.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>A Vietnam business visa, also known as a business visa, is a document issued by the Vietnamese government that allows foreign nationals to enter Vietnam for business purposes, such as attending conferences, meetings, or trade fairs, or exploring business opportunities. Business visas do not allow the holder to work in Vietnam or receive payment from a Vietnamese company. Business visas are typically valid for one to three months and can be extended upon expiry.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Application Requirements</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To apply for a work visa, the applicant must have a job offer from a Vietnamese employer and meet the qualifications and experience requirements for the job. The employer must also obtain approval from various authorities, such as the Department of Labor, Invalids, and Social Affairs (DoLISA), the Ministry of Labor, Invalids, and Social Affairs (MOLISA), and the People&#39;s Committee in the province where the company is located. The applicant must also provide a valid passport with at least six months of validity remaining, a police clearance certificate from their home country, and a health certificate. To apply for a business visa, the applicant must provide a valid passport with at least six months of validity remaining, a completed visa application form, and a letter of invitation from a Vietnamese company or organization. The letter of invitation must specify the purpose of the visit, the intended duration of stay, and the company&#39;s contact information. In summary, a Vietnam work visa allows foreign nationals to work legally in Vietnam for a specific employer, while a Vietnam business visa allows foreign nationals to enter Vietnam for business purposes. Both visas have different eligibility criteria, duration, and application requirements. It&#39;s important to carefully review the requirements and restrictions of each visa before applying. If you&#39;re unsure which visa to apply for, it&#39;s recommended to consult with a professional immigration agent or lawyer.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Obtaining a Vietnam work visa can be a complex process, but with the right information and guidance, it&#39;s possible to navigate the requirements and restrictions successfully. It&#39;s important to do your research and ensure that you meet all the eligibility criteria before applying for a visa. If you&#39;re considering working in Vietnam, we recommend consulting with an immigration agent or lawyer to help you through the application process and ensure that you&#39;re meeting all the necessary requirements.</p>\r\n', NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Vietnam Work Visa: Everything You Need to Know', 'Vietnam is a popular destination for foreigners seeking employment opportunities in Southeast Asia. The country\'s rapid economic growth and relatively low cost of living make it an attractive option for those looking to live and work abroad. However, obtaining a Vietnam work visa can be a complex process, with various requirements and restrictions to navigate.', 'en-vietnam-work-visa-everything-you-need-to-know', 'vietnam work visa', NULL, 93),
(143, 'vn', 'All the information you need to know about Vietnam visa extension and renewal', 'If you\'re planning a trip to Vietnam, you\'ll need a valid visa to enter the country. But what if you want to stay longer than your visa allows? Fortunately, there are options for extending or renewing your Vietnam visa', '<p>If you&#39;re planning a trip to Vietnam, you&#39;ll need a valid visa to enter the country. But what if you want to stay longer than your visa allows? Fortunately, there are options for extending or renewing your Vietnam visa. In this article, we&#39;ll cover everything you need to know about Vietnam visa extension and renewal.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Types of Vietnam Visas</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Before we dive into the details of visa extension and renewal, let&#39;s review the different types of visas available for Vietnam:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tourist Visa: This type of visa is suitable for those who plan to visit Vietnam for tourism purposes. It&#39;s valid for up to 3 months, and you can extend it for an additional 3 months.</li>\r\n	<li>Business Visa: This type of visa is for those who want to conduct business in Vietnam. It&#39;s also valid for up to 3 months, and you can extend it for an additional 3 months.</li>\r\n	<li>Work Visa: This type of visa is for those who plan to work in Vietnam. It&#39;s valid for up to 1 year, and you can extend it for an additional 3 years.</li>\r\n	<li>Student Visa: This type of visa is for those who plan to study in Vietnam. It&#39;s valid for the duration of your studies, and you can extend it as needed.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Now that you know the different types of visas available, let&#39;s explore the options for extending or renewing your Vietnam visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vietnam Visa Extension</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Applying for a visa extension is a process that enables foreigners to extend their stay in Vietnam without the need to exit the country. Once approved, an extension stamp will be added to their passport, indicating their new authorized stay duration. It&#39;s worth noting that a visa extension is only valid for single entry purposes.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vietnam Visa Renewal</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Visa renewal and visa extension share similarities as both options enable foreigners to extend their stay in Vietnam without the requirement to leave the country.<br />\r\nIn contrast to visa extension, visa renewal involves obtaining a new visa sticker and stay duration stamp on the passport, reflecting the updated duration permission. As a result, the visa renewal fee is typically higher than the visa extension fee, as it includes both the stamping fee and visa sticker fee.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Visa Extension/Renewal Requirements</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To extend/review your Vietnam visa, your original passport must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Be valid for at least 06 months from the time of extension/renewal.</li>\r\n	<li>Have at least 02 blank pages.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>What are the reasons to opt for a visa extension?</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The only choice is to continue remaining in Vietnam legally after your visa expiry date without leaving the country</li>\r\n	<li>Save your cost as the extension fee is much cheaper than the renewal fee.</li>\r\n	<li>Avoid being taken into the blacklist of the Vietnam Immigration Department because of overstaying.</li>\r\n	<li>Have more time to settle your business in Vietnam which might be interrupted if you leave Vietnam and then come back with a new visa.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Where to Extend Visa in Vietnam?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Hanoi immigration office: 44-46 Tran Phu, Ba Dinh District, Hanoi<br />\r\nImmigration office in Da Nang: 78 Le Loi, Thach Thang, Hai Chau, Da Nang<br />\r\nImmigration office in Ho Chi Minh City: 196 Nguyen Thi Minh Khai, Ward 6, District 3, Ho Chi Minh city<br />\r\nWorking hours: Monday-Friday (Morning: 7am &ndash; 11h30am; Afternoon: 1h30pm &ndash; 5pm) and Saturday (Morning time only)</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to extend Vietnam visa?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two options for obtaining a visa extension: applying directly at the Vietnam Immigration Department, or utilizing our Vietnam visa extension service for a more convenient process.<br />\r\nIf you choose to utilize our<a href=\"/all-the-information-you-need-to-know-about-vietnam-visa-extension-and-renewal\"> visa extension service</a>, the process of successfully extending your visa can be achieved in just three simple steps.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Step 1</strong>: Send us a soft copy of your passport and the page containing your current Vietnam visa and we will inform you whether your visa can be extended or not</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Step 2</strong>: Send your original passport to our address and pay the extension fee</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Step 3</strong>: Get your passport with extended stay within 8 working days normally or 3 working days in urgent case upon your request</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vietnam Visa Extension Cost and Duration</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The visa extension in Vietnam can be applied for the types of visas below:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Extend original visa exemption for up to 1 month</li>\r\n	<li>Extend original 1-month tourist visa for 1 month</li>\r\n	<li>Extend the original 1-month business visa for up to 3 months</li>\r\n	<li>Extend original 3 months tourist visa for 1 month;</li>\r\n	<li>Extend the original 3 months business visa for up to 3 months</li>\r\n	<li>Extend the original 5 years visa exemption certificate for up to 6 months</li>\r\n	<li>Extend original e-visa for up to 3 months</li>\r\n	<li>Extend 1-year tourist visa for US passport holders (tourist/business) for 1 month</li>\r\n	<li>Extend 1-year business visa for US passport holders for up to 3 months</li>\r\n	<li>Extend the temporary stay of APEC Business Travel Card holders for up to 3 months</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em><strong>Disclaimers:</strong> </em>Despite our efforts to maintain accurate and current information, it is possible that there might be changes of which we are unaware.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'All the information you need to know about Vietnam visa extension and renewal', 'If you\'re planning a trip to Vietnam, you\'ll need a valid visa to enter the country. But what if you want to stay longer than your visa allows? Fortunately, there are options for extending or renewing your Vietnam visa', 'all-the-information-you-need-to-know-about-vietnam-visa-extension-and-renewal', ' Vietnam visa extension, Vietnam visa renewal', NULL, 94),
